title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in pie crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add Jell-O.
Cool glaze and pour over strawberries.

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Combine garlic and the rest of ingredients in at least 3-quart baking dish.
Add chicken pieces, turning chicken and spooning mixture over while turning.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: lambrosian shanks
directions: Slowly brown lamb on all sides in oil; drain off excess fat. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over lamb.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until lamb is tender, turning occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: skillet supper
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add potatoes and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage and cook until potatoes are brown and tender.
Add green pepper and corn.
Cook until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: robert's delicious chocolate candy
directions: You mix it up in a bowl; pour it in a pan.
Then you have to set the timer.
You put it in the freezer for 10 minutes for the timer.
In the morning, it has to be mixed up.
You know it's ready when the dark is over, and the next morning, then you get all the ingredients to make it.
No fingers in the chocolate and not in the peanut butter.
The next morning, the chocolate and the peanut butter go in the freezer for 10 minutes.
Take it out of the freezer.
You have to set the timer before it rings. You got to knock on the chocolate to see if it's hard or not that hard. If it's supposed to be 5 minutes, 5 minutes is the low one to make it not that hard.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain and cool.
Add all ingredients; mix and stir.
Refrigerate.
Serve when thoroughly chilled.

title: baked rice custard pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in saucepan.
Mix just to moisten rice. Bring quickly to boil over high heat.
Remove from heat.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, mix together eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add hot rice mixture slowly, mixing well.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 35 minutes, stirring after 10, 15 and 20 minutes of baking. Remove from oven; cool.

title: play dough
directions: Wash seeds from pumpkin.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet. Toast at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle with salt. Eat.
Crunchy!

title: italian spiced potatoes
directions: Heat oil in frying pan and add potatoes and rest of ingredients.
Cook on low enough heat to keep potatoes from burning, and high enough to avoid mushiness.

title: wendy's frostee
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Dissolve soup mix with water. Add with roast to crock-pot. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook roast on low for approximately 8 hours. Add carrots and potatoes for approximately 1 hour.

title: kartoflane kluski(potato dumplings)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Roll out dough on floured board to pencil thickness. Cut into 2-inch strips and drop into boiling, salted water.
When they float to the top, they are done.
Arrange on platter and garnish with chopped, crisp bacon.

title: banana pudding
directions: Peel and slice bananas. Alternately layer bananas and vanilla wafers, starting and ending with vanilla wafers in a dish.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine rice, butter, onion, soups and milk in bowl, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli and cheese.
Spoon into greased 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°. Bake uncovered until golden brown.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: spicy barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes.
Ribs may need to be turned 1/2 way through cooking time (remove grease).
Remove ribs; drain well and brush both sides with mixture of 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon Creole seasoning.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Place on grill, basting with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Cook about 20 minutes.
May also be cooked in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: connie's strawberry delight
directions: Pinch angel food cake into pieces.
Put a layer of angel food cake, then vanilla instant pudding, then jello, then frozen strawberries, then layer with Cool Whip.
Repeat steps until you fill a glass dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place strawberries on top of Cool Whip.

title: apple crunch
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
With pastry blender, thoroughly cut in butter until mixture looks like crumbs.
Cut apples into slices.
Put apples in baking pan; sprinkle with walnuts.
Pile mixture on top.
Bake until tender, about 55 minutes at 350°.
Place under broiler to brown top lightly.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Beat egg in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rise 1 hour.
Make into rolls and let rise another hour.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and put in saucepan.
Add milk and syrup to cocoa mixture and mix.
Let mixture boil 1 minute (no more).
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Serve over ice cream while warm.
Store in a glass jar and reheat in the microwave.

title: hot cider
directions: Bring to boil and simmer.
Serve hot.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter together and put in an 8 x 10-inch dish.
Pack firmly, saving 2 tablespoons for the top. Beat cream cheese, dry Dream Whip and powdered sugar until creamy. Place creamed mixture into crumb crust.
Spoon one large jar of cherry pie filling over the top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients and refrigerate overnight add bacon and dressing when ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies with pudding
directions: Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixing bowl. Beat until creamy and smooth. Add eggs. Mix flour and soda. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Batter will be stiff. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: white chili
directions: For less spicy, use 1/2 block shredded Monterey Jack and 1/2 block shredded Monterey Jack with jalapenos.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of 8x8 pan, add
one can chili then shredded cheese, but not all of it, add other can of chili and remaining cheese on top.
Cook at 350 for 20 min. or until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add vanilla, salt, milk, sugar and oleo. Add potatoes.
Mix well and pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: spanish town seasoning mix
directions: Mix all above ingredients together. Store in covered jar in cool, dark cupboard. Good with beef and pork (use according to taste).

title: helen's chicken with rice
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Place uncooked rice in pan.
Arrange uncooked chicken over rice along with carrots and celery, cut in 1-inch pieces.
Pour chicken broth and stewed tomatoes over all.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: delmarva oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters of liquid and pour into saucepan.
Bring to a boil; skim foam from top.
Add oysters and simmer until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Remove from heat.
Heat milk and let it almost come to a boil.
Add butter, salt and pepper to oysters. Add milk to oysters.
Serve hot with oyster crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and put in buttered casserole. Mix crushed cornflakes with 1/4 to 1/2 cup of melted butter and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti(serves 14)
directions: Brown meat and onions in bacon grease.
In another pan, add 3 cans tomato soup plus 1 can water, then add pepper and juice drained from olives.
Let boil until sauce thickens.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Put in big dish. Mix meat, sauce, cheese and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Add spaghetti and mix well.
Spread mushroom soup on top and then sliced olives. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: frankfurters montgomery
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare noodles to package directions. Drain. Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, seasonings, juice of lemon and a strip of lemon rind.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove lemon rind.
Arrange frankfurters over noodles in large greased baking dish and pour sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water until dissolved (warm).
Mix all ingredients together, place on floured board.
Knead well, cut into biscuits about 1/2-inch thick.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 425°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and meal with a fork, then add the unbeaten eggs.
Add other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes or until firm in center.

title: barbara's mini cheesecakes
directions: Butter 4 sets of miniature tins.
Coat with graham cracker crumbs, shake off crumbs that did not stick.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into above.
Fill tins almost full.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.
Mix sour cream, sugar, vanilla, put teaspoon in top of each cheese cake.
Top with cherry half.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°.

title: potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, then mash, adding Mozzarella, margarine and cheese.
Keep mixing until Mozzarella and potatoes get stringy. Then take 9-inch pie pan lightly sprayed with Pam or cover with olive oil (just wipe on with paper towel, then cover with bread crumbs lightly).
Add potato mixture until pan is full, then top with rest of bread crumbs.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and soda last.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Add ice ring or ice cubes. Makes approximately 40 (4 ounce) cups.

title: squash puppies
directions: In a small saucepan, cook squash in just enough water to cover them until tender.
Drain and mash squash.
After mashing squash, drain again.
Combine squash, onion, egg, flour and cornmeal.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: campfire apples
directions: Peel apple; put on roasting stick.
Hold over coals until hot and softened around outside.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Slice off chunks of apple and eat!
Hold remaining apple over coals and repeat!

title: cabbage and ground beef casserole
directions: Chop cabbage.
Brown beef and drain excess fat.
In a casserole dish, place a layer of raw cabbage, then a layer of beef and alternate until dish is full.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a shaker jar; shake well until combined.
Pour half of this mixture into a dish; set remainder aside.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crockpot and cook on low for 8 hours.
Shred chicken with a fork and use for tacos, enchiladas, etc.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except peppers. Place in cavity of green peppers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Combine the mix with the water in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water; cook until thick.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or longer.
Add butter.
Add several spoonfuls of pudding to beaten egg; mix with remaining hot mixture.
Cook over hot water a little longer.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add vanilla.
May be filling for pies or cakes; also may be served as a plain pudding.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir while cooking.

title: grandma churchill's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Stir in chocolate chips and coconut.
Refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash and dry as many Irish potatoes as you like.
Line pan with foil.
Place potatoes in pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 400° until done.
Take potatoes out and let cool.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out the inside with spoon into a Pyrex dish.
Mash like cream potatoes and add pepper, salt and margarine or butter as you like.
Also add milk to make consistency you like.
Return this mixture to potato skin and top with slices of cheese and bake in oven until cheese has melted.
You may eat the skins if you like.

title: cloud salad
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add prunes, vanilla, eggs and milk until blended.
Add to mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast tex-mix muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin tins with Pam.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add cheese, eggs, buttermilk and salsa. Blend until moistened. Fill tins.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes; some ovens, 15 minutes (do not overbake).

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix together, flour, butter, egg, and pudding. Pour into a greased pie plate. Place the peaches in a circle affect on top. (Reserve Juice.)
Beat cream cheese, sugar and peach juice and pour over top of peaches, leaving it away from the sides of the pie plate. Bake at 350°F. for 20-25 minutes until golden brown.

title: cheese spread
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Blend and whip until fluffy. Spread on sourdough bread or French bread.
Bubble under broiler.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients right into 8 or 9-inch ungreased cake pan.
Make 3 impressions.
Put vinegar in one, vanilla in second and oil in third.
Pour cold water over all.
Mix with fork until dryness disappears.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Frost with white or chocolate icing.

title: wonderful pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cherries, pineapple and food coloring in a pan and cook until thick.
Add jello and cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with whipped cream before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage stuffed won tons
directions: Mix, fill, pinch and sit into muffin pans (make bottoms flat). Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: orange slice bar
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Then add dry ingredients, orange slices and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into bars.

title: hot pancake topping
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan. Stir in honey and raspberry preserves.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Serve hot over pancakes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: molded vegetable relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar and grated onion.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in vegetables.
Pour into 3 or 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Cook oatmeal in 2 cups water for a minute.
Add molasses, salt, butter and sugar.
Mix well and cool until lukewarm; add yeast that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Pour over flour.
Mix well and knead.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Knead and mold into 2 loaves.
Let rise until doubled. Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush crust with butter after you remove from pan.
Cool and wrap airtight.
Freezes good.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Boil milk, sugar, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Put all canned things together and add meat. Layer chips in bottom of pan, add layer of meat mixture, then chips and layer of meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put potato crowns in a 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom and sides. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cheese spread is sold loaf style in grocery stores.
Cube cheese and stir in tomatoes.
Microwave or heat on stove until cheese is melted and liquid enough to use as dip.
Best used with Tostitos or corn chips.
For variation, add cooked hamburger meat to dip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, pudding mix and orange drink; stir well.
Mix with fruit.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Add milk and vanilla to first 3 ingredients.
Blend in flour, salt, baking powder and blueberries.
Sprinkle top with remaining ingredients mixed together until crumbly.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons flour and ginger.
Coat pork with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Fry pork until brown; remove from skillet.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple syrup to measure 1 cup.
Shake remaining flour and the syrup-water mixture in a tightly covered container.
Stir flour mixture, vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce into fat in skillet. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; reduce heat.
Stir in sugar, salt, pepper and pork.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender (about 45 minutes).
Add pineapple and green pepper; cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in bean sprouts, water chestnuts and chili sauce.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 5.

title: pot roast in electric skillet
directions: Brown roast on both sides.
Turn skillet to 300°.
Cook 2 hours.
Put in vegetables.
Add soup and water, salt and pepper to taste.
Turn to 350°.
Cook until vegetables are done or you can put this in crock-pot overnight on low.

title: clam cheese dunk
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Remove from refrigerator about 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers and chips.

title: patty's potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes and eggs for about 35 minutes or until done. Drain the potatoes and eggs; then mix pickles, pickle relish, chow chow, bell pepper, green onions, olives, yellow onions, mayonnaise, mustard, hot sauce, salt, black pepper and red pepper in with the potatoes and eggs.

title: quick spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, tomatoes, onions and bacon; toss lightly. Serve with dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mamie's marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large heavy pan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour at once over chocolate mixture.
Stir with a wooden spoon until chocolate is melted and creamy.
Pour in a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour blueberries, drained.
Pour on top of blueberries the undrained crushed pineapple.
Next add box of dry cake mix.
Do not mix.
Next dribble melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure out desired amount; add soda and sift again. Set aside.

title: dump salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water completely.
Dump remaining ingredients into jello and mix well.
Chill and let set.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in butter.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook 20-30 minutes, until chicken is done.
Add picante sauce, rice and corn.
Cook 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly-roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease and flour the wax paper.
Sift the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt.
Beat eggs and sugar in a large bowl until thick and fluffy. Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once.
Pour into prepared pan, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Loosen cake around edges with knife.
Invert onto clean, damp towel dusted with 10xx powdered sugar.
Peel off wax paper, trim 1/4-inch from all sides.
Roll up cake and towel together from short side.
Place, seam side down, on wire rack; cool completely.
Unroll cake; spread with cream cheese filling. Re-roll cake and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: maple mustard country ribs
directions: Place onion rings in slow cooker. In small bowl combine syrup and mustard. Spread over ribs. Place ribs in cooker over onion. Cover, cook on low setting for at least 8 hours. Serve with additional mustard.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked pears
directions: Place pears in a baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thickened.
Spread sauce over pears and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt oleo, stir in cornstarch and seasonings.
Add cold milk and cook on medium heat until it begins to thicken.
Stir occasionally, then turn off, leaving saucepan on unit until mixture thickens.
Pour over sliced potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: boston cream croissants
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl and add pudding.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes. Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Split croissants horizontally. Fill with pudding mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: betty's special chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together; set this aside in bowl. Bring oleo, Hershey's cocoa, water and shortening to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over the sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add buttermilk with baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust(great for cream pies)
directions: Mix ingredients together; press into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with orange sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and paprika; brown lightly in margarine.
Add orange juice, rind and tarragon.
Cook in slow oven for 30 minutes. When done, remove chicken and cook sauce over high heat to reduce volume.
Serve sauce over chicken and/or steamed rice.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp in lemon butter
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add next 8 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are pink.
Makes approximately 4 to 6 servings.

title: foslaine
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and seasonings; drain grease. Add mushrooms, tomato soup and Mexicorn.
Cook noodles and drain. Put cooked noodles in an oven-safe dish and cover with meat mixture.
Cut cheese into sticks or, if grated, pour over top. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot bread and salad or a green vegetable and the table is set!

title: amy's favorite griddle cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Fry pancakes in a skillet with vegetable oil, or cook in a well greased waffle iron.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, adding apples and nuts last. Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or at 325° for 35 minutes in a glass pan.

title: pasticotti(italian christmas tarts)
directions: Combine sugar and shortening.

Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients with the milk to make a soft dough. Roll out on lightly floured board 18-inch thick to fit lightly greased tart cups or muffin tins. I use Pam and have no trouble with them sticking.
Use your fingers to press dough into the tart cups.
Fill with cream filling and cover with dough to fit.
I use a water glass that fits the top of the tart container.
Seal edge thoroughly and brush with 1 egg yolk, beaten with 1 tablespoon of milk.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: fudge chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Slowly beat in confectioners sugar.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 11-inch pan, while preheating oven. Combine all other ingredients.
Add melted butter; mix well. Return to pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: raisin filling for danish rolls
directions: Mix together raisins, vinegar, sugar, 1 1/2 cups water and salt and cook for 10 minutes, then add the 1/4 cup water and cornstarch to thicken. Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients. Let cool.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, peppers, onions, salt and garlic into ice water for 1 1/2 hours.
Boil sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar to a boil, then add drained pickles.
Stir off heat until they turn different color.
Put in sterilized jars, turn upside down and leave until sealed.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until mixture is combined.
Cool and fold in next 4 ingredients. Pour into dish and chill.

title: shrimp rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute butter, lemon, green onion and shrimp.
Serve over rice and enjoy.

title: quick jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and onion together in a deep skillet; drain off grease.
Add package of wild rice with water amount on box. Simmer until rice is done.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In casserole dish, spread cream cheese in bottom with spoon. Spread beans on top, then salsa. Top with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork oriental stir-fry
directions: In skillet, stir-fry pork on medium-high 4 to 5 minutes.
In large bowl, toss pork with remaining ingredients.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: vegetable log
directions: Mix and shape in log.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
This also makes a delicious easy vegetable sandwich spread.
I mix pecans in with other ingredients for this.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach dip or spread
directions: Defrost frozen spinach or chop fresh spinach.
Place in strainer and press water out.
Add other ingredients and mix.

title: sweet chili meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together. Form 1 inch balls.
Cook in covered pan; drain off grease. Mix chili sauce and grape jelly. Pour over meatballs and simmer until desired consistency. Serve with toothpicks.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together flour, white sugar, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
In one hole, pour vanilla.
In next hole, pour liquid shortening.
In last hole, pour vinegar.
Over all pour cold water and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 X 13 pan and bake 45 minutes at 300 degrees.
This cake need not be iced.

title: rowdy dowdy
directions: Blend, then add 1 egg.
Put fruit in bottom of dish.
Use peaches or blueberries, etc.
Pat with butter.
Put topping on. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 375° in a greased iron skillet until brown.

title: peach coolie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Alcohol of choice can also be added.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together and put into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 regular size loaf pans, 3 medium size pans or 5 small size pans.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Set aside but keep warm. Next combine melted butter, 1/3 cup Pet milk, cake mix and nuts (this is very stiff).
Press half of the cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been lightly oiled.

Bake at 350° for 6 minutes exactly. Remove from oven and sprinkle the package of chocolate chips over the cake. Drizzle the caramel mixture over the chocolate chips and press the remaining cake mix over the caramel.
Bake this for 16 minutes (no more and no less) at 350°.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Pour the water into a small, warm bowl.
Sprinkle the yeast and the pinch of sugar over the water.
Stir the mixture and let it stand in a warm place until the yeast bubbles, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute mushrooms, butter and celery.
In large bowl stir together spaghetti, sauteed ingredients and the remaining ingredients.
Place in greased dish and put paprika over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbling.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Mix the onions, cheese and tuna well together; spread in an unbaked pie shell.
Mix the eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over tuna mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: pate brisee tart shell(pastry for orange tarte recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until hot.
Serve with crackers.
Heat at 350° in oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening together until crumbly. Add egg and water.
Mix well. Roll out on floured surface.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned. Glass pie pan does best.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine pudding, Jell-O, water and lemon juice in saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pour into mixing bowl and chill until mixture is thickened.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip, blending well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped topping and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Mix and shape first 4 ingredients into 70 little balls.
Put in single layer in large baking dish.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popped corn in 1 large turkey roaster.
In a 2-quart saucepan put oleo, brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, stir and pour over popcorn until all coated.
Put into a 250° oven for 45 minutes, stir every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper to cool. Store in Tupperware, it keeps good.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix sour cream and celery soup.
Stir in 1/2 cup of melted butter.
Add hash browns.
Spread ingredients in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: walnut brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet with butter.
Put all ingredients in large pan.
Cook until you can make a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Pour onto cookie sheet and cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tamalitos
directions: Arrange Tamalitos in pan and heat to desired temperature.

title: clain roberts' favorite dish
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and spread on bottom of medium baking pan.
Mix soups and sour cream and spread over chicken. Crumble crackers and spread evenly over top mixture.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes.
Serve hot.
This is not a dish for dieters, but it is great!

title: hush puppies
directions: Saute onion in a little butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease.

title: grandma's famous arkansas dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in 2 tablespoons butter or oil until tender.
Add chicken broth.
Add corn bread (crumbled up) and one slice of bread (broken in small pieces), salt, pepper, parsley and eggs.
Cook on top of stove until set.
Turn in greased pan and bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 30 minutes).

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix together wheat flour, unbleached flour, brown sugar, baking powder, and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into Pam sprayed muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: poor man casserole
directions: Drain noodles and mix all together.
Cook until heated all through.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top before serving.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugars and egg.
Add baking soda and flour.
Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Prepare ziti as label directs.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage and turkey until well browned, stirring occasionally. Stir in Ricotta, next 3 ingredients and half of spaghetti sauce. Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over mixture.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a bowl, mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening; sprinkle in water, mixing with a fork. Gather dough together and press into a ball. Proceed as directed for any two crust 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: chicken stir-fry whip up
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook meat and Miracle Whip for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Stir in soy sauce and garlic powder.
Continue cooking 5 minutes or until meat is done.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown the pork chops in oil. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat juices run clear. Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Make batter out of first ten ingredients.
Chop and add last 4 ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
(Or a little longer, 35 minutes until firm and lightly browned.)

title: fruit rice salad
directions: Cook rice in the 2 cups of water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add the other ingredients when the rice is cool.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar substitute and spices until well blended.
Stir in eggs and gradually blend in skim milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake until done at 400° about 40 minutes.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Will need small paper baking cups.

title: spicy garlic chicken pizza
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: pistachio heaven(it's heavenly good!)
directions: Make pudding according to box directions.
Empty Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Mix. Mix 3/4 bag of marshmallows into pudding Cool Whip mixture.
Decorate top with remaining marshmallows.

title: chicken creole style
directions: Prepare the rice as directed on package.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop hearts.
Mix in mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in casserole dish (small). Crunch croutons on top. Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: nancy's mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order of recipe. Use 9 x 13 Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour mixture in pan. Bake 35 minutes until cornbread is light brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Best if made the night before.
Put paper towel on top of salad in refrigerator to keep it from getting watery.

title: low-cholesterol oat bran raisin muffins
directions: Made with no added fat or sugar, these tasty muffins use fruit and buttermilk to keep them moist.

title: barbecued flank steak
directions: Crush clove of garlic and combine with other ingredients. Marinate meat or chicken overnight.
Broil on grill 10 minutes on each side.

title: apple pecan bread
directions: Bake in a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple, apple and orange. Sprinkle gelatin and instant pudding on top of fruit and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken lo mein(low-fat)
directions: Bone chicken breast, saving skin and bone.
Slice meat into thin slices/strips.
Simmer skin and bone in 1 1/4 cups water and bouillon cube for 15 minutes; strain into cup; add water if necessary to make 1 cup liquid.
Boil linguini or vermicelli. Heat sesame oil in wok or large skillet.
Saute chicken strips until golden in color.
Add chopped scallions and saute for 1 minute longer.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce, and stir until thick and clear.
Fold in bean sprouts, 1 1/2 cups lettuce and cooked vermicelli.
Heat on low and stir until lettuce is wilted and the mixture is well combined.
Serve with remaining lettuce and chopped pimiento.

title: ham and potatoes casserole
directions: Mix
together and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: pecan butter cookies
directions: With electric
mixer
or
food
processor cream butter, brown sugar, egg,
vanilla,
baking
soda
and cream of tartar until smooth and
creamy.
Stir in flour, pecans and chocolate chips. Drop
by
heaping
teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: jeri's salad dressing
directions: Put sugar, mustard, garlic powder and salt in mixing bowl and set on medium speed.
Add vinegar and oil gradually.
If you rotate vinegar and oil slowly and beat, it will become creamy and thick.
Stir in celery seed and onion.

title: apple square cake(no eggs)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake in tube cake pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Add milk.
Stir in egg and oil.
Stir in mashed banana.
Pour batter by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a hot nonstick griddle.
When brown on one side, turn and brown other side.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter shake
directions: In blender, combine milk, Nestle Quik and peanut butter; blend until smooth.
Add ice cream.
Makes three 8-ounce servings.

title: fresh brisket roast
directions: Place brisket on large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup, 2 1/2 tablespoons liquid coffee, 2 1/2 tablespoons water and sprinkle liberally with soy sauce.
Fold up in foil with drugstore fold.
Bake in a 250° to 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Cool; slice across grain.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix (let butter cool a couple of minutes before adding to dry mix). Mixture should be crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture for topping. Pat remaining crumbs mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme and spread evenly over mixture in pan. Crumble the reserved crumb mixture over the peanut butter/marshmallow. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool; cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen 1 1/4 inch bars.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix
Jell-O,
pineapple
and water together in saucepan and boil
until
Jell-O
is dissolved.
Set aside until cool. Add
1 cup buttermilk to cooled mixture and beat until frothy. Fold
in container
of
Cool Whip.
Pour into square dish and chill.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: no knead oatmeal bread(2 loaves)
directions: Can add 1/3 cup of wheat germ when flour is added.

title: garlic pasta
directions: Cut the garlic into thin slices and saute in the olive oil until not quite browned.
Add the cream, tiny bit of salt and ample pepper.
Simmer for a moment to reduce the cream and then toss with the hot pasta.
Add cheese and parsley garnish.

title: microwave candied pecans
directions: Place butter in a 1-quart round bowl.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in nuts until well coated; microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread out on foil to cool.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs high speed 1 minute.
Add sugar and lemon juice, beating well.
Then add sugar, salt and spices.
Fold in flour. Add pumpkin until done well. Pour on greased cookie sheet (sprinkle nuts).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn cake on towel (powdered sugar on towel).
Roll up and let cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs and mayonnaise together.
Add chopped onion, cheese, water chestnuts and mushroom soup.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in casserole and top with crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Brown chicken breasts on each side in a butter (margarine) and oil mixture.
Place in roaster pan(s).
Brown shallots in butter. Add half and half gradually heating and stir constantly.
Add wine and continue heating until warm.
Add mustard and whisk until thoroughly mixed.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover roaster. Bake chicken at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and flour. Deep fry until golden brown.
Place the chicken in another pan and add a mixture of soy sauce, sherry, water, ginger, green onion and sugar.
Heat the pan (or wok).
Add chicken and other ingredients. Stir slowly until sauce begins to dry up.
If it dries up too quickly, add a little more water.
Great the next day for a picnic.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and sharp cheese together with hands.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika. Place garlic buds in ball.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Remove at least 1 hour before serving.
Remove garlic buds.
Serve with crackers.
This freezes well.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs, stir in vanilla.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Roll dough on floured surface, cut in circles using glass or cookie cutter.
Use pie filling or any type of fruit fillings.
Two circles per cookie, 1 for top; 1 for bottom.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Roll into logs. Chill overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Brown beef; add seasoning and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add flour and brown.
Add milk and stir (more milk can be added if thinner consistency is desired or substitute part water if milk gravy is too rich).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter a 8x8-inch pan, and set aside.

title: orange rice
directions: In medium saucepan, bring the orange juice to a boil.
Stir in the butter, sugar and rice, combining well, then cover tightly. Simmer the rice over low heat for about 18 minutes.
Do not lift the cover or stir.
Remove from heat.
Add the orange zest and stir.
The rice should be tender and the liquid absorbed.

title: shrimp appetizer spread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Add sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well. Spread mixture on a round 12-inch serving latter. Sprinkle with shrimp. Top with seafood sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, green pepper, tomatoes and onions. Cover and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs next, then remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Warm sugar and cocoa on low heat 2 minutes.
Add butter and blend in milk.
Increase heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Use over cake or ice cream.

title: skor cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 baking dish by spraying with Pam spray.

title: lemony layer bars
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Stir until dough forms. Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine pudding and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Spread over dough in pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour cabbage salad
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, celery seed, vegetable oil, salt and mustard seed and pour over cabbage.
Let stand 24 hours before using.
Will keep for 3 weeks.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients with about 1/2 cup cold water.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Dough should form a ball.
Roll 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Cut into bones.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
For dogs.

title: melonade slush
directions: Place half of watermelon in a food processor bowl with metal blade or blender; process until smooth.
Pour puree into a 2-quart nonmetal freezer container.
Repeat with remaining watermelon.
Add lemonade and limeade concentrates.
Stir to blend.
Add ginger and vodka; stir to blend.
Cover.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight until firm; stir once or twice.
Remove from freezer 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
For each scoop serving, one cup.

title: fried cinnamon pies
directions: Mix together cinnamon and sugar.
Make up pie crust with water, lard and flour.
Roll out enough to fold over after putting filling inside and flute edges (good), so won't leak out when frying.
Put filling inside and fry in skillet until golden brown on each side. Only makes 1 pie or 2 small ones.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla, almond and eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, mixing well. Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This cake freezes well.

title: marcie's waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients lightly.
Use all the batter.
Freeze or reheat leftovers (if any).

title: lemon chicken with fettucine(servings:  10)
directions: Grate zest from lemon and set aside in small bowl.
Squeeze lemon juice over chicken pieces and let marinate for a few minutes, turning chicken once or twice.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together and coat chicken pieces.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in nonstick skillet and saute for 3 to 4 minutes per side. Remove chicken and add remaining butter and flour mixture to form a paste.
Pour any remaining lemon juice marinade and chicken broth into cooking pan, loosening brown bits, making a gravy. Return chicken to pan and sprinkle with lemon zest and brown sugar mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or simmer same amount of time.
Serve over cooked fettucine.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos into small crumbs.
Melt the butter and combine with the crushed Oreos.
Spread into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Save a few crumbs for a sprinkling on top.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put a layer of cucumbers and onions and a layer of ice.
Then sprinkle salt over it and let it stand for 3 hours.
Then heat sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and celery seed.
Then heat and let boil until sugar is dissolved.
Let it come to a boil good.
In the meantime drain cucumbers and onions and put in jars. Pour mixture in jars.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into 10 equal portions.
Pour oil into skillet.
Brown each piece of steak.
Transfer to a roasting pan.
Add onions to oil in the skillet and brown lightly. Add the rest of the ingredients to make a barbecue sauce and stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour the sauce over the steaks in the pan. Cover.
Bake 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
(Baste meat occasionally with sauce in pan.)

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook light brown sugar with milk.
Boil until it's thin in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Remove from fire and leave until cold.
Then beat until creamy.
If sugar curdles the milk, add a pinch of baking soda.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Make 3 cooked layers.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Spray 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Place all ingredients in blender, food processor or mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute; pour into sprayed pan and bake approximately 50 minutes until center puffs out and knife comes out clean.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Cream cheese and sugar with egg yolks.
Trim crust from bread and roll each slice with a rolling pin until flat.
Spread cheese mixture thinly on each slice of bread.
Roll up bread and dip in margarine.
Roll Blintz in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place them on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 48 Blintzes.
Do not thaw before baking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs in mixing bowl. Beat in sugar and oil. Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Add zucchini and vanilla. Stir well. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: ultra low-fat taco meat
directions: Brown meat in Teflon skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add onion and brown a little longer.
Add salsa and mix well.
Add taco seasoning and cook to desired consistency.
Serve hot, rolled in flour or corn tortillas, or chill and serve cold on top of tossed salad for a taco salad.
If using meat for filling in a tortilla, add chopped lettuce and tomato and 1 tablespoon lite sour cream.
Entire recipe makes 6 servings.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Stir in milk into soup.
Add cooked chicken, 1/2 the cheese and macaroni.
Mix well.
Place in a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and stir.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths, roll each piece of biscuit into mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Drop into pan after coating with cinnamon and sugar.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Serve with small pieces of party rye bread, sourdough bread or Hawaiian bread.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut meat small in chunks; mix all ingredients in skillet or wok.
Add sauces and all other vegetables.
Cover; simmer until tender.
Make a thickening of the cornstarch and enough water to make a smooth paste.
Add to beef mixture.
Continue to simmer. Makes a nice gravy that can be served with rice.
Season with salt and pepper to your taste.

title: squash cakes
directions: Add squash, egg, sugar, salt, butter and milk to a bowl and mix.
Add yeast mixture and flour and blend.
Cover and set aside to rise.

title: quick coffee cake(hungary)
directions: May substitute peaches for the prunes.

title: bran chex muffins
directions: Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake at 400° in greased muffin tins for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 6 large or 12 small muffins.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and apple in food processor or kitchen food grinder.
Add remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and beaten eggs.
Add puddings, Bisquick alternately with the milk.
Then add chocolate chips.
Bake about 10 minutes in scant 375° oven.
Makes about 2 dozen or more.

title: breaded veal steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces.
Dip into egg with milk, then into breadcrumbs mixed with salt and paprika.
Fry veal in heated fat in heavy skillet until well browned.
Pour 1/2 can of soup mixed with milk over meat.
Cover and simmer (do not boil) 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove veal from pan.
Pour remaining soup, thinned with milk, into pan.
Stir, heat and serve as sauce.

title: oven fried or broiled fish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip fish in milk and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place in
lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
You can use any kind of fish fillets.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix cream cheese with pineapple juice.
Whip thin; add pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows. Cool in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.

title: quick company apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice apples in an 8 or 9-inch pie pan. Mix remaining ingredients until the mixture resembles crumbly pie dough.
Add 1/4 of the mixture to the apples in the pan.
Stir until evenly distributed.
Top the pie with the remaining.
Bake pie in oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown. This is excellent served with ice cream.

title: viennese apricot pie
directions: Combine eggs, sour cream, sugar, flour, salt and extract; beat with rotary beater until blended.
Stir in apricots, drained and cut into pieces.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with topping.
Return to oven for 20 or 25 minutes, until filling is set.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In frying pan, chop and slice chicken breasts into small pieces.
Mix in corn after chicken breasts are cooked thoroughly, then put a small amount of picante sauce in.
Stir and then simmer. Spread cream cheese on tortilla shells.
Put chicken and corn mixture in middle of shells.
Slice a couple strips of Monterey Jack and place on top of mixture, then put on Mozzarella cheese. Fold shell and close with toothpick.
Place in foiled cookie sheet. Sprinkle a little Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When done, serve with picante sauce poured over top of each fajita.
This recipe makes 4 to 5 fajitas.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Toss apples, sugar and spices together lightly. Add flour, soda and salt to apple mixture.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, oil and vanilla. Add to apple mixture.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Put on Lemon Glaze. Cut in squares.

title: glazed doughnuts
directions: Mix in order given; let rise 2 times to double in bulk.
Roll out, cut and fry in hot grease.
Frost with 2 pounds powdered sugar mixed with water.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Place jelly and mustard in pot and heat slowly; stirring until well mixed and jelly is melted.
Cut hot dogs into small pieces. Add to sauce and simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: danish apple pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Turn
into	lightly greased pie pan.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done. Serve warm or cold, topped with whipped cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and onion rather small.
Cook in water 5 minutes and drain.
Add soup, sour cream and shredded carrots and melted margarine.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of oiled 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top.
Distribute remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is pretty and delicious!

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Add ham and roll up.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Over the top, sprinkle 1/2 cup white sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serve warm or cold.

title: vanilla wafer cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light in color.
Add cream cheese gradually.
Add vanilla.
Put small cupcake liners in cupcake pans.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner and pour mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.
Serves 14.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice fruit in large bowl.
Mix the peanut butter, mayonnaise and juice from cherries.
Stir until smooth; pour over fruit.
Add the marshmallows; stir until well mixed.

title: easy chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, Tabasco and chicken spread.
Roll into ball and roll in walnuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped mushroom casserole
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
In large frying pan in which you have placed the butter, cook until all water in mushrooms has disappeared.
Saute until lightly browned.
Roll out crackers, using rolling pin.
Butter a 10 x 10-inch deep casserole. Alternate layers of mushrooms and crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls. Chill until firm. Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls in the chocolate mixture.

title: waffle
directions: Mix all except egg whites. Stir until smooth. Beat egg whites separately and fold in. You can add your choice of fruit.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing.
Wash and prepare fresh vegetables and mix English peas with them.
Add dressing. Stir to coat vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Put your steaks in the oven at about 325° until they are done. Take them out and drain the steaks.
On the bottom of your pan, put the Stove Top stuffing on the bottom.
Put steaks on top.
And then put the mushroom soup on top of the steaks.
Then put back in the oven for about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift the flour; measure and resift 3 times with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add bananas and mix.
Add flour in 4 portions and beat until smooth after adding each portion.
Turn into a well-greased pan (8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch) and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool on rack before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole. Melt butter, crush crackers and mix together.
Spread over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrots with garlic and basil
directions: Place carrots in a glass pie plate with 2 tablespoons water. Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave on High for 3 minutes. Coat large frying pan with nonstick spray.
Saute carrots, garlic, basil and lemon juice until fragrant, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: fall cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add brown sugar and Bisquick.
Mix well. Add vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: bronia's meat loaf(abington grange supper)
directions: Mix all together and place in a loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken or crab souffle
directions: Butter 2 slices bread, cut in small cubes and set aside.
Cut the remaining bread in 1-inch cubes and put in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Combine chicken or crab meat, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasoning and spoon over bread.
Put remaining unbuttered bread cubes over mixture.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Cover and chill an hour or overnight.
Spoon soup over top and sprinkle with butter cubes.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 50 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle cheese on top last few minutes of baking.

title: strawberry country dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, jello and 1/4 cup milk together until smooth; add Cool Whip.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown chopped onion and chopped green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef and cook until crumbly.
Add tomatoes and soup.
Season to taste. Simmer while macaroni cooks.
Drain macaroni and mix with meat.
Put in casserole and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Layer bread cubes, chicken and shredded cheese in well-greased casserole. Mix eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour mixture over chicken mixture.
Let set 5 to 6 hours. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar mints
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and blend thoroughly together.
Add heated milk and flavoring.
Press small amounts into molds.
Remove at once to wax paper.

title: pineapple fizz
directions: Just mix all ingredients, adding sherbet last.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Mix juices from fruits and pineapple with vanilla pudding. Mix in with fruit in a bowl. Chill at least 1 hour. Now can be served over pound cake.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Stir in soup and water.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese chocolate cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup Crisco and vanilla together. Measure 10x sugar.
Blend half of sugar in cream cheese mixture. Add hot water.
Add chocolate until smooth and rest of 10x sugar. Take out 2 cups of mixture for icing.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together all except Hoffman or cocktail sauce and spread on plate.
Then spread on Hoffman or Kraft shrimp cocktail sauce. Sprinkle on 6 diced crab sticks.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soups and milk; stir until blended. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: homemade graham cracker crust
directions: Mix together.
Press into a pie pan and fill with favorite pie filling.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Blend flour, margarine and remaining ingredients.
Mix with mashed carrots and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place into baking dish.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg, flavoring, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread crumbs and raisins.
Mix well and pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla, then add sifted ingredients and milk.
Roll and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake on baking sheet in moderate oven (375°) for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: my dark secret
directions: Soften gelatin in orange juice; heat to dissolve.
Stir in coffee.
Combine with evaporated milk in small mixing bowl.
Put in freezer until mixture begins to freeze.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in large bowl for 2 minutes.
Beat in chocolate.
Beat evaporated milk mixture 2 minutes.
Fold in chocolate.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Brown onion in bacon drippings.
Blend in soup, milk, salt and crumbled bacon.
Add potatoes and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a slightly greased covered casserole for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let stand at least one hour before serving.
Serve with chips or with tacos, fajitas, etc.

title: pesto tomato toast
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Place bread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread each slice with scant tablespoon of pesto.
Top each with tomato; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 8 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: spinach and penne
directions: Cook penne according to package directions; make it al dente.

title: carrot nut loaf
directions: Mix ingredients; put in a sprayed pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Have ready a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and 2 mixing bowls.
In first bowl, beat cake mix, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and butter together and pour into greased pan.
In second bowl, beat powdered sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla until creamy. Pour over first layer in pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and margarine together until it thickens slightly.
Add pineapple; mix and pour into partly cooked crust. Bake until it sets.

title: montine (wilcox) purkey's dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seasoned baked pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over all pretzels.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn often while baking.

title: granny's fresh apple cake
directions: Peel, core and chop up apples.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, apples, water, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into an oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini, set aside.
In another bowl, mix together the flour, salt, baking soda and powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and nuts.
Gradually blend second mixture into first mixture until all is blended.
Bake in 2 loaf pans in 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf from 1941
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook at 350° about an hour or until done.

title: nicole's favorite chip dip
directions: Mix all together.
Add cream in thirds.
May not need the whole half-pint.
Serve with chips.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches and place in crust.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, melted margarine and flavoring.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until custard is thick and crust is brown.

title: ground beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion rye bread
directions: Place all ingredients in automatic bread machine pan; press start. Allow to cool 30 minutes before slicing.
(Sure!)

title: rum ricotta pudding
directions: Blend Ricotta and milk.
Add sugar and rum; mix well until custard consistency.
Place in serving dishes; chill.
Just before serving, dust with powdered instant coffee.
Serves 25.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish. Coat chicken with cooking spray; dredge in cereal mixture. Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray and coat chicken again with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown. Contains 170 calories (21% from fat) per chicken half.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter.
Add flour and chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add milk and cream.
Add ham and peanut butter; simmer for 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add cooking oil and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add grated carrots.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours; for layers bake 30 minutes, for sheet cake bake for 20 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream
all
ingredients.
Refrigerate to make it easier to handle.
Make
logs desired size.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and egg well.
Then add milk and butter. Microwave on High for 2 minutes at a time, stirring between times until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Alternate layers of sliced bananas, wafers and sauce.
Serve while still warm.

title: black olive dip(single batch; makes a lot.)
directions: *Any of these Ro-Tels may be changed to make the dip hotter if you want.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)
Ice brownies in the pan while they are still hot.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Cut up onion and peppers into very small pieces.
Add all other ingredients and cook for 1 hour or until thick.
Put into jars and seal.

title: veggie enchiladas
directions: Wash and bake the potatoes for 1 hour in a 400° oven.
While the potatoes are baking, remove the casings from the sausage. Crumble and fry the sausage meat in a large Dutch oven with onion until both are cooked through.
Pour off any grease.
Add stewed tomatoes and Monterey Jack cheese to the sausage mix and set aside. When potatoes are done, remove from the oven and split in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the potatoes; mash slightly (leave them lumpy) and add to sausage mix.
Place the skins on a cookie sheet and fill with the mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and return to the oven for 15 minutes or until warm through.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on whether or not some are teen-agers!

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars and marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler; cool thoroughly.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold the whipping cream into the chocolate.
Pour into crust.
Place in the refrigerator at least 3 hours.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Can be frozen.

title: punch
directions: Boil water, then add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Then add lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice and stir to mix. Freeze.
When ready to serve, add Sprite or ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: english parmesan muffins
directions: Set oven control to broil.
Spread margarine on muffin halves. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Cut each muffin half in half.
Place in broiler pan and broil 4-inches from heat for about 2 minutes or until light brown.

title: orange pecan sweet potatoes
directions: With a mixer, blend the sweet potatoes, margarine, sugars, honey, 1 cup of pecans, 1/2 cup of coconut and orange juice, still frozen.
Whip all the ingredients until smooth.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Take the rest of the pecans and coconut and spread over the top.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until firm. Remove and garnish top with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows are melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla extract, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Stir cherry pie filling, semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove and add sugar.
With a wooden spoon, stir until well blended.
Return to low heat.
Stir rapidly until thoroughly mixed and begins to bubble.
Add water and syrup; mix well. Cook to 290°.
Remove at once and sprinkle in nuts and mix quickly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and spread out.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces when cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Mix in beaten eggs and vanilla. Add salt.
Activate baking soda in water and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing well.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for about 8 to 10 minutes.
For softer cookies, remove before they "look" done. Cool a bit before on sheet and then completely on racks or wax paper.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill for an hour; then serve.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Let sausage get to room temperature.
Mix Bisquick, butter and milk.
Divide dough in half and roll out on floured surface. Spread rolled dough with half of sausage.
Roll sausage and dough mixture like a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper, freeze about an hour and slice thin.
May freeze in roll or slices.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: oven hash browns
directions: Mix.
Place in an 11 x 17-inch dish.
Add 1 cup crushed corn flakes or potato chips as topping (optional).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken with chicken bouillon cubes, pepper and bay leaf. Dice cooked meat.
Place diced chicken in a 13 x 5-inch Pyrex dish. Pour over chicken the melted margarine.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Heat the soup and chicken broth to boiling.
Pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Boil onions, celery and pepper until 3/4 cup of liquid remains in pan.
Combine all ingredients including water from vegetables, except catsup.
Bake for 1 hour at 360°, then remove from pan and drain water from the meat loaf.
Spread catsup over the loaf and return to oven for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: spinach bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes (until cheese browns on top).
Loosen edges immediately after removing from oven.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and freeze.
Stir it twice as it freezes.
Freeze overnight.
Take out in the morning and thaw all day in the refrigerator to serve in the evening.

title: sauteed onion and apples
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onions and apples. Cook 10 minutes covered, stirring occasionally. When apples are soft and onions slightly browned, add salt and pepper.
Serves 4 as a side dish.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well and pour in baking dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add pineapple and juice.
Let set several hours or overnight (overnight best).

title: alabama chili
directions: Heat the fat and quickly brown the beef and add the onions. When onions are translucent, add the rest of the ingredients. Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until needed. Better if it sits awhile.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix oregano, basil, red pepper, onion soup mix and water in a jar.
Shake vigorously until thoroughly blended.
Pour over meat. Bake in medium low oven for 4-5 hours or until tender or you may use a slow cooker.
After meat is done, shred well with a fork. Sprinkle mild pepper juice over meat and cook longer to blend flavors.
Serve on buns or french bread with peppers.
This freezes well.

title: one minute bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients except cucumbers in enamel pan and let come to a light boil.
Add cucumbers and let come back to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal tightly.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes at simmering temperature.
Makes 2 pints.

title: finger paint
directions: Bring 3 cups water to boil.
Using food coloring, color water. Add cornstarch, stirring until dissolved.

title: frioles refritos(refried beans)
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a heavy frying pan.
Add several spoons of beans and using a fork, back of a spoon or pastry blender, mash beans as they are cooking on low heat.
Add more beans and continue smashing until frying pan is fairly full and the beans are creamy.
Remove to a large bowl and continue with the next batch until all beans have been refried.
Freezes well in meal size batches, using Ziploc bags.
This is a tasty and inexpensive alternative to canned refried beans used in Mexican dishes.

title: quick millionaire pie
directions: Mix well, pour into graham cracker crust and chill about 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large bowl, combine chips, butter and marshmallow cream. Set aside.
In a pan, combine sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over mixture in bowl and stir until smooth. Place in buttered baking dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for a couple of hours.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Let Cheddar and cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Combine salad dressing mix, mayonnaise and milk in mixer bowl; mix well.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese and ham; mix well.
Chill, covered, in freezer for 30 minutes.
Shape into ball; coat with almonds.

title: * brownies *
directions: Melt chocolate; add sugar, eggs and flour.
Bake at 350° for 26 1/2 minutes.
This is the secret.

title: wild blueberry jam
directions: Measure fruit into 6 or 8-quart pan, along with lemon juice. Measure sugar into separate bowl. (Scrape extra sugar from cup with spatula to level or exact measure.) Add Sure-Jell and butter to fruit. Bring mixture to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Quickly add sugar to fruit; bring to full rolling boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Skim off foam. Fill jars, tighten and invert 5 minutes, then turn upright. After 1 hour check seals. Or use USDA water bath method.

title: gloria's broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain.
Add cream of broccoli soup and your salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until cream of broccoli is hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: slumgullion
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Put onions into skillet to cook. Add meat.
Cook on high.
Add lots of chili powder, salt slightly.
Stir in noodles with water.
Add tomato sauce and a little more water.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Stir just enough to keep from sticking.

title: pumpkin apricot loaf
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix pumpkin and water. Sift salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
Fold sifted ingredients into egg mixture, then add pumpkin mixture.
Lastly, add nuts and apricots.
Divide mixture into 3 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Shape into balls. Place in baking pan.
Pour 2 cans golden cream of mushroom soup over balls.
Bake at 325° until well done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, water and cinnamon.
Spread with flour, sugar and butter.
Bake
at
for 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Grate or grind cucumber, onion and bell pepper.
Grate the carrots.
Put together and squeeze out juice, saving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Add gelatin to the 3 tablespoons of juice. Put in a double boiler and heat until melted.
Add to vegetables; fold in mayonnaise and mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Refrigerate overnight to blend the flavors.
Makes 3 dozen party sandwiches.

title: chocolate candy cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Lower heat under saucepan and stir in chocolate chips. Stir until completely melted.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Run cranberries through chopper.
Also run oranges and apples through chopper.
Add sugar to mixture and set aside.
Mix boiling hot water with jello.
Let cool.
Combine jello and fruit mixture. Use 9 x 13-inch dish for this.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 12.

title: nielsen's apple cheese wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare the wild rice.
Simmer the onion and celery in the 1/4 cup water about 5 minutes.
Add this, with the water, to the rice. Stir the soup until smooth and stir this and the cheeses into the rice.
Either on stove top or in a casserole in the oven, cook until heated through, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add the apple pieces and continue to cook another 15 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-0s with boiling water and set to cool (just syrupy). Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
