title: gooey batter cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, melted butter and 2 eggs by mixing by hand.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 egg and confectioners sugar and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli-peanut stir-fry
directions: In medium bowl, mix well 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, sherry, 2 tablespoons water and the sugar.
Add beef; toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or up to 1 day.

title: susu's party hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain off fat.
Cut cheese into small cubes and add it and seasonings to meat.
Mix until cheese almost melts.
Spread on bread slices.
Freeze on cookie sheet and then store in plastic bags in freezer.
Either broil or heat in hot oven until they brown on top when ready to serve.

title: canned fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour batter over margarine.
Pour fruit over batter and sprinkle with raisins and dates.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat in hot fat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning; simmer 2 hours.
Add water if necessary.
Add beans; heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix altogether; let set 15 minutes before you put mixture in a 9-inch double crust and bake for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix pineapple juice, broth, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Bring to a boil. Mix cornstarch with a small amount of water. Add to boiling mixture and cook until thick. Add green pepper, onion, pineapple and cubed pork. Let cook about 3 minutes. (Do not overcook; pepper and onion should be crisp.) Serve over rice.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks and oil.
Add flour, cinnamon, pineapple (not drained) and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in cold oven at 300° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: royal rice custard
directions: Cook rice in 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salt until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Scald the milk.
Beat the whole eggs and yolks slightly with the sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and almond extract.
Add the scalded milk gradually to the egg mixture, then stir in rice.
Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: christmas date pie
directions: Arrange dates evenly on bottom of pie shell.
Combine the next 10 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat with a rotary beater until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pie shell over dates. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool before serving.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: In casserole, layer shrimp, mushrooms and almonds.
Top with 1/2 of sauce.
Repeat.
Cover with cracker crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in a covered jar in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles in a large pot for 15 minutes with 1/2 cup oil and salt to taste.
Drain; then run cold water over noodles.
Separate and lay on a large plate.
Saute ground meat until brown.
Drain grease.
Saute onions and sausage together; when about done, add mushrooms.
When done, drain grease off.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread about 2 tablespoons beans on each tortilla.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in chicken.
Spoon 1/3 to 1/2 cup down the center of each tortilla; top with 1 tablespoon cheese each. Roll up and place seam side down in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over the top; sprinkle with onions, olives and remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Just before serving, sprinkle lettuce around enchiladas if desired.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: cranapple relish
directions: Shred the apple in a food processor or hand grinder.
Quarter the orange and combine with cranberries in processor or grinder. Process until coarsely chopped.
Blend the apple, cranberry mixture, coriander and sweetener together.
Put in covered dish and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Sprinkle onion salt in pie crust.
Mix chicken and Swiss cheese.
Place
in pie crust.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly. Stir in milk and corn oil.
Mix in cornstarch, salt and pepper until well blended.
Pour over chicken-cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Before making this cake, put milk, eggs, margarine and Crisco out on counter and let come to room temperature.
Mix together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and flour alternately. Add flavorings and salt.
Put mixture into tube pan.
Place in cold oven and set temperature at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When cake is done, set pan out to cool, for about 5 minutes.
Invert on cake platter.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook butter, flour, milk and salt for 5 minutes.
Add cheese. Stir until it melts.
Fold in broccoli and onion.
Fold in well-beaten egg yolks.
Lightly fold in egg whites that are beaten fluffy.
Set dish in pan of water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Make a paste with cocoa and vinegar.
Add butter mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add buttermilk and cake coloring.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.

title: pound cake
directions: Work flour, baking powder, sugar and margarine like pie dough. Add milk, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: In heavy duty mixer or food processor, mix everything but the pecans until well blended.
Refrigerate until it can be shaped or put into a mold.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: united nations sandwich
directions: Layer in this order:
1 slice of Italian bread (spread with French dressing), 1 slice of Swiss cheese, 1/2 of the sauerkraut, American cheese, lettuce leaf and tomato.
Top off with pickles and spread Russian dressing on top piece of bread.
Put on top piece of bread and put it into a Ziploc sandwich bag.

title: canned green beans
directions: Break green beans.
Wash and pack each can.
Add teaspoon of salt per can; fill with water.
Put flats and rings on; tighten rings.
Put 2 quarts of water in canner.
Put cans in pressure cooker.
Bring to 10 pounds pressure; cook for 25 minutes.

title: black butter catfish
directions: Poach catfish fillets for 6 to 8 minutes in barely simmering water to which you have added a touch of white wine and two lemon slices.
Carefully lift the fillets to a plate to drain.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and blend with Bisquick and sausage.
Roll in very small balls, the size of a dime.
Bake at 300° to 325° until brown.

title: cassava cake
directions: Mix grated cassava with evaporated milk and condensed milk together in the baking pan.
Beat eggs and add to mixture in baking pan.
Add melted butter and macapuno.
Add 6 to 8 teaspoons sugar, if desired.
Mix well and cook in oven for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat in a saucepan on top of the stove until hot; add cheese and stir well.
Cool and serve.
May be kept in refrigerator a couple of days.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Beat egg white with salt until soft peaks form.
Add brown sugar in 2 additions, beating lightly after each.
Stir in nuts and drop 2-inches apart from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil in skillet.
Stir in onions, rice, beef broth, one soup can of water and the soy sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in peppers and pimentos; heat thoroughly.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Makes 20 cups (with champagne).

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Cook rice separately.
Put sausage back in frying pan.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; fry until done.
Add water, soups and rice; stir.
Bake in a casserole dish, covered, for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
The temperature should be 350°.

title: orange marmalade lamb shoulder roast
directions: Insert garlic into roast.
Combine marmalade, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour over lamb and let stand 4 hours in refrigerator, turning frequently.
Reserve marmalade mixture.
Place roast on rack in a 325° oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes per pound.
During last 30 minutes of baking, baste roast with marmalade mixture until done.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil together sugar, water, shortening and raisins for 5 minutes.
When cool, add dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: holiday mold
directions: Boil tomato soup (do not dilute).
Add cream cheese, gelatine, peppers, onions and shrimp.
Mix well.
Fold in gently the mayonnaise.
Set eight to ten hours in fridge.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Place cherry pie filling in a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Cover with yellow cake mix.
Pour oleo over cake mix. Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: limas with a twang
directions: Put your
beans in a 2 quart baking dish.
Mix mustard, Worcestershire
sauce,
vinegar, tomatoes, brown sugar, onions and 2
slices of diced bacon.
Put over beans.
Cut bacon into 4 pieces
and
lay on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes to an hour. Serves 4.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a crock-pot.
Mix together onion mix, apricot preserves and Russian dressing.
Pour mixture over chicken and cook on low-medium until chicken is tender.

title: watermelon in ginger wine
directions: Shape watermelon into balls using a round melon baller; removing seeds from melon as necessary.
When all melon on top surface has been shaped, cut off top using a long sharp knife. Scoop out the exposed surface of melon.
Combine melon balls in large bowl.
Combine water, wine and sugar in small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves and mixture is hot.
Remove from heat.
Cut ginger into thin slivers.
Stir ginger into wine mixture.
Pour over melon balls.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Spoon watermelon and wine mixture into bowls.

title: greek chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Quarter potatoes and put around chicken.
Put all the seasonings and Crisco on and around chicken and potatoes.
Then slice lemons and squeeze on top of chicken and potatoes.
Cover with foil and cook at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: kentucky dixie pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar, add eggs and butter, stir well. Add vanilla, nuts and chips and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300 degrees for 45 min.
Rich but delicious.

title: green beans(for diabetics or people on a diet)
directions: Drain green beans.
Put in saucepan and pour a diet Coke over. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Very good.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bottom of 6-cup percolator. Place spices in basket of percolator.
Let mixture come to a full perk.
Let perk for 3 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk, egg and fat.
Mix lightly. Arrange fruit in bottom of baking dish.
Spread with butter.
Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) until brown.
Serve with vanilla, lemon or fruit sauce or cream.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Boil potatoes 20 to 30 minutes with 1/2 teaspoon salt and water to barely cover.
Drain and mash.
Combine first 9 ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into six patties.

title: pecan pilaf
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet (medium heat).
Add pecans, saute 10 minutes.
Remove pecans, cover and set aside.
In same skillet, melt remaining butter.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Add rice and stir thoroughly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into one large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Chill.
Serve at room temperature. Good with all kinds of crackers.

title: lizzies
directions: Put raisins and bourbon in bowl.
Mix well; let stand 1 hour. Sift
together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; reserve.
Put butter or oleo in large bowl of electric mixer
and add
brown
sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixture is light
and fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture with mixer or spoon, blending until smooth.
Stir in raisins, citron, cherries and pecan halves.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake
in slow
oven
about
15 minutes or until firm. Remove
to wire
racks
to
cool.
Makes 7 to 9 dozen.
Store cookies airtight.
Can be frozen.
Good keepers, shippers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Whisk eggs with sugar.
Add cream.
Pour into pumpkin and mix well.
Add seasonings and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Preheat oven to 375°.
After cooking for 10 minutes, turn pies 1/4 turn and lower temperature to 350°.
Set timer for 1/2 hour and check again.
Check every 10 minutes until pies are firm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and cool.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, pimento, pickle relish, chopped eggs, mayonnaise, mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blackberry breeze pie
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in cold water and refrigerate for 1 hour or until thickened. Gently fold in blackberries and whipped topping. Pour into crust. Chill for 2 hours or until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: butter roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly
grease a 7 x 11 inch baking dish.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells. Bake at 325° for 45 min. For best results let sit for 1 hour or more before eating.

title: sausage and cheese cocktail rye
directions: Brown sausage and drain well with paper towels. This is really important so they won't be greasy. Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave. Mix in with sausage and blend well. Place cocktail rye on cookie sheet. Put heaping tablespoonful of mixture on cocktail rye. You can make these ahead of time and freeze on cookie sheet, then put frozen bread in freezer bags. Place in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly. You can also put under the broiler for 3 to 5 minutes, but watch carefully.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar together.
Let it soak overnight in the refrigerator.
Beat the eggs and add the sugar and eggs to the mustard mixture.
Put in a double boiler.
Heat to boiling.
Stir a bit.
Let cool and put in fridge.

title: orange slush drink
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled water/sugar mixture.
Place in empty Cool Whip or butter containers and freeze overnight.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add sugar, lemon juice, rind, cornstarch and milk.
Cook over a slow heat until thick.
Cool.
Put into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar for meringue. Put on pie and brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients; excellent for veggies.

title: sparkling punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients; mix until sugar is dissolved.
Chill for 1-2 hours.
Just before serving, stir in soda.

title: gayle brown's baked curried chickensaladserves 6
directions: Mix chicken, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice in 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Melt margarine, stir in bread crumbs, paprika and curry; sprinkle over casserole.
Just before serving, sprinkle crushed peanuts and coconut over dish.
Can freeze before adding peanuts and coconut.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour, then add a little flour at a time until consistency to drop by teaspoonfuls into deep grease over medium flame.
Dry until golden brown, then drain on paper towels.

title: merry sherry
directions: Heat sherry with 1 stick cinnamon and sugar just to boiling. Add lemon juice and pour into preheated cups.
Add thin slice of lemon to each cup with cinnamon stick for stirring.
Makes about 5 or 6 servings.

title: cheesy onion rounds
directions: Cut circles of slice bread in small circles about 2 to 2 1/2 inch rounds. Spread with mayonnaise and cheese mixed well. Top with thin slice of onion same size as bread round. Place under broiler until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: aunt julie's cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, sugars and eggs.
Cream well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix; add corn flakes, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin; mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin mixture.
Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs and add melted butter or oleo.
Firmly pack 2/3 mixture in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix crumbs and butter in a 9 inch pie pan; press firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy beef dip
directions: Combine drained beef, cheese, milk, dill weed and horseradish and chill.
Serve as a dip.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in enough water to cover them until tender.
Add remainder of ingredients; stir until cheese melts and soup thickens slightly.

title: manicotti
directions: Blend cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, sugar and parsley.
Put sauce in bottom of pan.
Fill shells.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 an hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add other ingredients in order, mix thoroughly.
Bake in layer cake pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pecans and coconut; sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Pour prepared cake mix over this.

title: 3-day coconut cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in 2 layers and cool; split into 4 layers.
(Dental floss is good to split cake.)
Mix fresh frozen coconut with sour cream and sugar. Set aside 1/2 cup of this mixture for later use.
Spread the rest between layers.
Mix the 1/2 cup mixture with the whipped topping; spread on top and sides.
Refrigerate 3 days in an airtight container before cutting.

title: aunt emma's apricot salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 2 packages of jello in 3 1/2 cups of boiling water. Add drained pineapple.
Let set to gel.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix salt, catsup, vinegar and brown sugar.
Stir into beef mixture.
Add beans.
Place in 2 casserole dishes.
Freeze 1 casserole for future use.
Bake remaining dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake as per instructions on cake box.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13 inch pan bake 20 minutes at 350°. Melt the caramels, oleo, milk and pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Add rest of cake mix on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250° and 10 minutes at 350°.
Needs no frosting.

title: sausage soup
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Meanwhile, brown the sausage and drain. Dice the potatoes and green pepper. Add to simmering mixture and cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a medium size saucepan over medium heat. Using a wire whisk, slowly blend in flour until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add milk, whisking constantly.
Whisk in salt and pepper and simmer over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cut potatoes in half, scoop out the meat and set aside.
Add potatoes to milk mixture.
Add sour cream and simmer, stirring to keep soup from sticking.
Garnish with grated cheddar cheese, bacon and green onions.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Set for 2 hours, then add 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water. Leave tea bags in water for 20 minutes, then remove. Add the rest of ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes. With strainer, remove spices.

title: no-peep stew
directions: Place meat in bottom of roasting pan and pour all other ingredients on top of meat.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover and cook at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peep while cooking.
Meat will be tender and you will have a good rich brown gravy for rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: very chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then stir in chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kelly's cookie kisses
directions: In a large bowl cream shortening, peanut butter, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to peanut butter mixture, blending thoroughly.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Place potatoes and water in a 2-quart microwave casserole. Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender; drain.
Mix mayo, sour cream and salsa.
Mix potatoes and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in mayo mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl and garnish with additional sliced ripe olives and shredded cheese, if desired.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and green onion in butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat, stirring to form large soft curds; when eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and Cheese Sauce.
Spoon eggs into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/4 cup melted butter and bread crumbs, mixing well; spread evenly over egg mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: country brunch
directions: Trim crust from bread and add cut slices in half.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Cover bottom with 1/2 of the bread, ham and cheeses.
Repeat with remaining bread, ham and cheese. Combine milk, egg and seasonings; pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Combine corn flakes and butter.
Sprinkle over dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken stew
directions: Flour the chicken.
In a large stock pot, brown the chicken in oil.
Add onions and cook until the onions are clear, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Cover and simmer until the chicken is almost tender.
Take the chicken out of the stew and remove the bones and skin.
Leave the chicken meat in fairly large pieces.
Return the corn and lima beans. Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.

title: apricot jello
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, sugar, egg, flour and butter. Add cream cheese.
Let mixture cool.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add to cooked mixture.
Spread on top of jello.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a clear bowl and serve with chips.

title: a b's bacon-coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in bowl (large).
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter in large bowl; mix together.
Cook sugar and Milnot together until it forms a soft ball (approximately 12 minutes).
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla; pour into Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix well together until creamy.
Pour into greased pan; let cool.
This candy cuts better if allowed to stand overnight.

title: my mammy's peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches in bottom of dish.
(You may use canned peaches if drained; I like Greer peaches best if fresh are not available.) Sprinkle with lemon juice to keep from darkening.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar and egg with fork.
Mixture will be dry and crumbly. Spread over peaches.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Recipe may be doubled.

title: baked french toast
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, beat eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and salt until light and frothy.
Add bread and let soak abut 10 minutes on each side or until mixture is absorbed, or cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: "mom's" pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and butter or lemon flavoring.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Preheat oven at 300°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all except strawberries in saucepan and cook until clear.
Place berries in baked pastry pie shell and cover with the sauce which has been cooled to room temperature.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs, then oleo, milk, flour, then nuts and mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift flour in
a
bowl, cut in shortening with a pastry blender, blending until
mixture
is coarse.
With a fork, add enough sour cream until all flour is mixed in.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly for 1/2 minute.
Roll out with rolling
pin
to
1/2-inch
thick.
Cut
with floured biscuit cutter.

title: grape plate pie
directions: Cook grapes with sugar enough to sweeten them good.
Then cook them until the syrup is thick and sticky.
Make your pie dough. Line your pie pan, prick crust.
Pour in grapes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, add cut up butter in little pieces.
Put on top and grease with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut holes in top crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is done, about 30 minutes.

title: cathedral salad(really a dessert)
directions: Mix jello with hot water only.
Blend in ice cream.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator at least 3 hours.

title: moving day soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a pot and bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mulligetawny soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to boiling.
reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cloves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: light spinach quiche
directions: Combine flour, eggs, and milk.	Pour over spinach and cheese in 9 inch deep dish pie crust.
Sprinkle on pepper and nutmeg to taste.
Bake 350° for 50 minutes.

title: deviled bacon
directions: Batter bacon and dip in bread crumbs; place on broiler pan flat and very close together (in rows).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and place in foil pan or freezer tight container on paper towels stacked sideways to fill container. Freezes well.
Reheat oven to 350° and remove bacon from freezer; let thaw 30 minutes and then bake for 20 minutes and serve.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: creamy chocolate meringue pie(club member: nicholas)
directions: Mix 3 egg yolks with 1 cup sugar. Stir until creamy. Sift cocoa, flour and salt together; add to egg mixture. Thin this mixture with 1/4 cup milk. Put remainder in 1 quart size copper bottomed boiler, stirring constantly, over direct medium heat. Let milk warm slightly, then add sugar mixture. Continue stirring until creamy. Add vanilla. Place in 9-inch baked pie shell. Make meringue with 3 egg whites, 6 tablespoons sugar and pinch of salt beaten together until sugar is dissolved and soft, but firm, peaks form. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shipwreck
directions: Grease a 9x11 casserole dish with margarine.
Make 1 layer of onions sliced, 1 layer of potatoes sliced thin, 1 lb. hamburger browned, kidney beans, tomato soup and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Grind unpeeled oranges and lemon in a food processor or grinder.
Transfer to a large kettle.
Add baking soda.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Peel the remaining fruit.
Grind and then crush it.
Add to orange mixture.
Measure and return to kettle.
Add sugar equal to the amount of fruit.
Boil until thick, about 30 minutes.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process for 20 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yields about 7 pints.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk in saucepan.
Stir in butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure water into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast into water.
Stir to dissolve.
Blend in milk mixture and eggs.
Stir in half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make soft dough, stirring until dough forms a ball that leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn onto floured cloth and press into flat ball.

title: mom's popcorn balls
directions: Stir over low heat until mixture boils.
Pour over popcorn in a large pan.
This is enough to coat 5 quarts of popcorn. Shape into balls.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, combine kidney beans, peas, corn, green beans and garbanzo beans. Stir in celery, onions and bell pepper. In a small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables. Mix well and refrigerate at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: jean's hamburg vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Mix broth, spices and tomatoes in a large pan.
Add meat mixture and remaining vegetables.
If too thick, add some V-8 juice.
This soup will freeze well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl on medium speed, scraping sides and bottom constantly until mixed (about 1 minute).
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, eggs and flour well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and golden brown.

title: egg and lemon sauce for soup
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and continue beating.
Then pour gradually, a tablespoon at a time, to the broth or stock.
Be sure to do this slowly and beat constantly so that the eggs will not curdle.
Pour sauce over the food and remove from fire at once and serve.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate. Spread cottage cheese over bottom of "crust."
Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until browned.
Drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic.
Heat.
Pour mixture into spaghetti "crust."
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top; bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts and browns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven baked fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut and wash chicken.
Dip in egg and flour.
Fry one side for 15 minutes.
Turn and fry 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix ingredients well, then knead with hands until it is smooth.
This is the only kind you can eat.

title: short ribs and potato dumplings
directions: Brown meat on all sides in own fat; pour off excess.
Add seasonings; cover with water.
Simmer.

title: chocolate mint shake
directions: Mix everything together in a bowl and beat with an egg beater. Serve in a tall glass.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple evenly over bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sift the cake mix over the fruit evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix. Distribute butter pats evenly over the mixture.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup, salt, flour and butter.
Cook on low heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir only long enough to blend well.
Then quickly pour into well buttered pan.

title: andy's marinated chicken
directions: Marinate 24 hours or more.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes on cookie sheets.

title: eula's indian potato salad
directions: Using a large skillet, fry bacon.
Drain bacon on paper towel.
Peel, cube and fry the potatoes in the bacon grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough to cover pizza pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake until bread tests done with a broomstraw or toothpick, or until browned.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
In the bottom of a greased Bundt pan, place the nuts.
Add the cake mix and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curried four fruit bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; add sugar and curry powder. Drain and dry fruits; put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add butter mixture.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate until needed.

title: triple orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jello; when dissolved, add orange sherbert.
When this begins to set, add other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold or dish.
Refrigerate.
Really good; make ahead.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Add onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and water. Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cook 30 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup cold water; stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.

title: netter's bonbons
directions: Melt milk chocolate in microwave or over hot water (low heat for both).	Mix butterscotch pudding with other ingredients;
form into small balls.
Put on wax paper to dry for 1/2 hour.
Dip each ball in chocolate; put back on the wax paper. Let dry for at least 1 hour.
Hide to keep.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes more or until set.

title: chicken ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add all other ingredients.
Mix in mixer.
Chill and shape into a ball.
Roll in sesame seeds or chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.
Garlic salt can be added for extra flavor.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Bake 10 minutes at 350° on cookie sheet.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mash hard-boiled eggs and mix with mustard.
Mix cracker crumbs and milk.
Cook for a minute, add melted margarine, eggs and mustard.
Stir; add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased dish (either square or medium size rectangular).
Sprinkle a few cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° until brown (about 40 minutes).
Two recipes will fill a 3-quart rectangular dish.

title: lasagna hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Add onion.
Add soups.
Mix together.
Boil egg noodles until done.
Mix noodles and other mixture together.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.

title: gladys king's pecan pie
directions: First, crack and break pecans into smaller pieces.
(Use a chopper or food processor).
Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Pour sugar, Karo syrup and eggs into a medium bowl and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Spread pecans in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Put in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until a knife is put in and comes out clean.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Place all fruit (drained) except cherries in a 2 quart casserole. Blend butter, sugar and curry powder over low heat. If mixture seems too dry add a little fruit juice.
Pour mixture over fruit. Decorate top with cherries. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hr.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: hawaiian seafood stir-fry
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Add shrimp and scallops; mix well.
In small bowl, drain juice from pineapple.
Add broth, 3 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
In large skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil; stir-fry seafood for 2 minutes and remove from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and heat.
Stir-fry green pepper, onion, carrots and ginger for 3 minutes.
Add seafood, pineapple and sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Beat eggs; add to milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread and add more milk, if too dry.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip, then all other ingredients.
Chill for several hours, then serve.

title: braised german cabbage
directions: Combine all in a large skillet, cover.
Cook over low heat 20-25 minutes.

title: broccoli country cornbread
directions: Cook unseasoned broccoli until tender.
Mix margarine, cottage cheese, Jiffy mix and broccoli.
Drop in beaten eggs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: regal chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, pineapple, grapes, peanuts and celery. Stir in the tarragon.
Salt to taste.
In another bowl, combine the mayonnaise, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Fold this mixture into the chicken-fruit mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Add liquid from raisins to all the ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan in 350° oven, 1 hour or until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix together sugar, pumpkin and eggs.
Beat well then add flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix all together real well, then pour on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top and bake for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a terrycloth that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar; let cool.

title: presidential enchiladas
directions: Remove seeds from chilies and chop them.
In large skillet, heat small amount of oil.
Add chilies and garlic and saute. Drain and break up tomatoes.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Add tomatoes, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano and reserved tomato liquid to the chilies and garlic.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove from the skillet and set aside. Combine the chicken with the sour cream, grated Cheddar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat 1/3 cup oil; dip tortillas in oil until they become limp.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings and soak in a small bowl of cold, salted water for about 30 minutes, then drain and dry them on paper towels.
Combine bread crumbs and poultry seasoning in a dish.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water, cold water and chill.
Mash one very large or 2 small very ripe avocado (in blender).
Add lemon juice, hot sauce and mayonnaise.
Add to jello; beat.
Let it firm.
When serving, place on top either in small hole molds or make with teaspoon.
Fill with fresh or frozen raspberries or strawberries depending on season.

title: company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap a piece of dried beef and one piece of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place wrapped chicken in a baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for another 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and soda, then add vanilla, oats, coconut and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: easy party fruit punch
directions: Mix frozen juice concentrates and water in punch bowl or other large container.
Five minutes before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes or ice frozen in ring mold.
Cut orange and lemon into thin slices, if used.
Float in punch.
Garnish with sliced strawberries and sprig of mint, if desired.
Makes 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: zap an apple
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Insert sticks into stems.
Microwave caramels and water in small deep glass bowl on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir after each minute until smooth.
Dip apples, turning until coated.
Place on greased waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Let stand
15 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Yield: 10 servings.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Mix in order.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and chicken (separately) until almost done; drain.
Combine broccoli, chicken, garlic powder, milk, mushroom soup, margarine and rice (if desired) in a large bowl.
Blend well. Pour into a long casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until ingredients begin to boil.
Uncover and bake until brown on top.
Let stand for about 15 minutes (uncovered).
Enjoy!

title: caramel apple crunch pie
directions: Combine the flour and salt. Using a pastry blender, cut in the shortening until pieces are pea size. Using a total of 6 to 7 tablespoons cold water, sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of the mixture and gently toss the mixture with a fork. Push the moistened dough to one side of the bowl. Repeat, using 1 tablespoon of water at a time, until all of the dough is moistened. Divide into thirds.

title: pineapple splash
directions: Combine all ingredients into the blender.
Blend well and serve chilled over ice or straight up.

title: spinach, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in buttered, 2-quart casserole with tight fitting lid.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is done.
(Baking time may vary depending on type of dish used.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening gradually.
Add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with cream and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.

title: apple crisp for two
directions: Put apples and water in 1-quart baking dish. In a bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and cinnamon. Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes. Garnish with whipped cream and cinnamon.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well as given.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: jelly cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Mix 1 tablespoon flour with soda, baking powder, and salt together to add to mixture.
Add milk, and mix together thoroughly.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Mixture will be very dry.
Grease and flour round cake pan and evenly spread 3 tablespoons batter into pan.
(If batter is hard to spread, use a spoon and a little water to spread in pan.)
Bake 10 layers of cake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Remove each layer immediately and spread with thick layer of plum jelly.

title: nana's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all sugar, vinegar, milk, water and margarine.
Cook until it begins a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Let simmer until it forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of the marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Add peanut butter by tablespoons until hard, then add remaining marshmallows and stir until mixed well.
(These won't dissolve completely.)
Pour into greased pan and cool.
Cut in block-size of your choice.
Makes approximately 9 x 13 pan.
Smaller size pan makes thicker squares.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain the salmon but save the liquid.
Remove bones from salmon.
Mash up the salmon.
Add 1 egg, salt, pepper and onion powder to taste.
Add enough bread crumbs until the mixture holds together (if its too dry, use some of the salmon liquid).

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil fruit 3 minutes; add shortening and cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Check at 10 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add ice cold milk and cream.
Beat with mixer until frothy.

title: chocolate zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Grate zucchini.
In a large bowl, combine flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In another bowl, combine zucchini with all remaining ingredients. Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean. Cool on a rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Make
a paste of cocoa and coloring.
Add to first mixture.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl.
Add to batter and blend.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle is clean.
Cool and frost.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cream oleo until light.
Gradually beat in sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until well blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, mixing after each addition only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fold blueberries into batter.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Unmold.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine margarine and milk; add dry yeast and sugar.
Using mixer, gradually add flour.
Do not knead.
Let rise in mixer bowl 45 minutes to one hour.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into three-inch squares.
Melt another stick margarine.
Dip each piece into margarine and arrange, overlapping, in a Bundt pan.
Let rise another 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, mashed bananas, frozen strawberries and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip and more nuts when congealed.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all together and make out in patties. Fry in a heavy frying pan that you have sprayed with Pam. Fry until done. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: heavenly pineapple pie
directions: Whip the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: hibachi
directions: Before you begin cooking be sure that the chicken, onions, zucchini, and mushrooms have been sliced into bite-size pieces. For the onion, slice it as if you were making onion rings, then quarter those slices. For the zucchini, first slice then into long, thin strips, then cut across those strips 4 or 5 times to make bite size pieces that are 1 to 1 1/2 inch long.

title: garden delight potato salad
directions: Drain Veg-All thoroughly and combine with potatoes, green pepper, sweet pickles, onions and chopped eggs.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chew bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg and spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Top each square with a pecan half.

title: baked chicken breast with spinach
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Pat spinach into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Dip chicken breasts into flour and then butter. Place on top of spinach.
Season well with salt, pepper and garlic. Pour whipping cream over spinach and chicken breasts.
Sprinkle generously with cheeses and dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat in a skillet. Place tortillas one at a time in a skillet with about a 1/2-inch of oil. When the tortilla bubbles, turn over. They will only take a couple of seconds to bubble. Place in an ungreased 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.

title: lemon chicken breasts
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Melt butter in heavy skillet and saute chicken until almost done.
Add mushrooms and olives and simmer over low heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and lemon juice, simmer 2 minutes more.
Remove to serving dish and sprinkle Parmesan and garnish with fresh parsley.

title: fruit juice pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 (9-inch) baked and cooled pie crusts.
Will set up right away.

title: blueberry goody
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch glass dish, layer blueberries and pineapple. Sprinkle with sugar.
Place dry cake mix over that, covering completely.

title: breath of spring salad
directions: Pour pineapple, with juice, into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in jello mix, stirring until dissolved.
Let cool.

title: delicious strawberry pie
directions: Put water, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Put on low heat and keep stirring until thick.
Add jello and let mixture cool.
Add cut up strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When cold, serve with Cool Whip.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap each 1/2 slice bacon around 8 to 10 beans.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in 7 x 10-inch baking dish.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup light Karo, brown sugar and margarine in a medium size saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until mix begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, stirring well until coated.
Press evenly into a 9-inch buttered pie pan.
(This will be the crust.)
Combine peanut butter, chocolate syrup and 3 tablespoons Karo syrup.
Spread 1/2 the mixture over the crust.
Freeze until firm.
Allow ice cream to soften slightly.
Spoon into frozen pie crust, spreading evenly. Freeze until firm.
Warm remaining peanut butter mixture and drizzle over top of ice cream.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to the directions on the package and pour into baking pan.
In separate bowl, mix together egg, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese and swirl into brownies.
Bake according to directions on brownie package.

title: potato salad with blue cheese and sour cream
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and cut into cubes.
Add parsley, onions, celery and almonds.
Mix together salt, sour cream, Blue cheese, pepper and vinegar.
Stir into potato mixture and marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with eggs and radishes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Place in the refrigerator for about an hour and serve.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and garlic salt together. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Melt butter; add garlic salt.
Brush on biscuits after baking.

title: texas-caviar
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl after chopping all veggies first. Pour dressing over all and toss.
Let marinate at least 2 hours. Drain and serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together in 2-quart saucepan on low.
Cool slightly.
Place cooked chocolate mixture, eggs, sugar and vanilla extract in medium mixing bowl.
Beat until well mixed and smooth.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with nuts to chocolate mixture.
Beat until blended well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: wedding punch
directions: Let ingredients soften a bit; mix together and serve.

title: chicken with rosemary
directions: Fry bacon until barely crisp; pour off fat and remove the bacon.
Brown breasts in oil and butter.
Add salt, garlic and pepper to pan when chicken is almost browned.
When browned, add rosemary and white wine to pan.
Add bacon; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix tomato paste with chicken broth; add to the pan. Cover; cook for about 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mrs. bonewell's bread(won "best of show" crawford county fair 1992)
directions: Mix sugar, oil, salt and water.
Add flour enough to beat into thick soupy mixture.
Sprinkle in the yeast.
Beat and add more flour.
Let rest about 15 minutes, then add more flour.
When thick enough to knead, keep adding flour a little at a time until dough is smooth and squeaks.
The more you knead, the finer the texture of the bread.

title: glazed stuffed cornish game hens
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Do not stuff hens until ready to roast.
Rinse hens in cold water; pat dry lightly. Stuff cavities with prepared stuffing.
Roast at 400° for 1 hour. Place any remaining stuffing in a small baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar until crumbles.
Set aside.
Cook flour, sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Add butter and vanilla; let cool.
Put 2/3 of peanut butter and sugar mixture in bottom of baked pie crust.
Add filling.
Put on meringue and then add rest of peanut butter and sugar mixture.

title: pickled pigs feet
directions: Cook
4 front pigs feet until you can take the meat off the bones
(use enough water to cover them).
Add a few Whole Spice, and
a
piece of onion, just to give it flavor.
Drain the soup off the meat, straining out the onion and spices. Cut up
the meat
into fairly small pieces, and put into separate dish, salt and pepper it as you like.
(We always put a little garlic powder,
just
a little, or use a piece of garlic with onion
when cooking
meat.)
Then pour the soup back over the meat,
but just enough to cover the meat.
Stir well, and set it on the cabinet or table until it cools.
Scrape off the fat or
grease, and discard that.
Cover the meat and soup mixture with
a
lid, put into the refrigerator (not freezer) until it settles good, or is firm, and can be sliced.

title: chicken puffs
directions: In saucepan, bring water and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture forms a ball (1 to 2 minutes).
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating until smooth and put small mounds on spoon and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut tops off and remove filaments.
Fill each with chicken salad. Replace tops.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix cherry juice, water, sugar and
cornstarch. salt and food coloring. Cook until thickened, stirring continually. Add cherries and heat through.

title: rice shrimp
directions: Peel and season shrimp with salt and red and black pepper. Saute shrimp and onion in oil.
Add rice and 2 beaten eggs.
Fry as desired.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; add onion, seasonings and water.
Add raw celery and carrots.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are almost tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together 3 times, add to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Divide into 4 parts. Roll out on well floured board into circles.
Pat into well-greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn warm in a 275° to 300° oven.
Combine corn syrup, sugar and salt in a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Cook without stirring for 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well. Pour syrup slowly over popcorn in a fine stream, mixing with a wooden spoon.
When cool enough to handle but still quite warm, shape into 2 to 2 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 12 to 18.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and put 1/2 of the cheese in batter, then put rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: polio con broccoli(chicken divan)
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salted water (1 teaspoon of salt), some celery and onions for about 1 hour.
(Save the broth as it makes good soup.)

title: mini cherry cheesecakes
directions: You will need foil cupcake papers.

title: quick bread mix
directions: *I
use my favorite self-rising flour and leave out the salt and baking powder.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a heart ring mold or 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter. Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well between each egg.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to egg and sugar mixture, beating between each addition.
Mix in vanilla and almond flavoring.
Pour into prepared pan and bake on center rack in oven at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes for heart ring mold or 25 to 30 minutes for round cakes or until tender.
Come clean.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Trip crown if necessary and invert on plate on rack to cool.
Outline the plate with whipping cream.
Fill in with canned cherry pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: paul lamping's best in the west chili
directions: *If you like it hot, add a lot.
If you like it mild, don't get wild.

title: poor boy chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together at one time.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lentil pilaf
directions: With oil, saute garlic and green onion in a stock pot.
Add celery and carrots, let the mixture saute for about 5 minutes. Add lentils, chicken broth, seasonings and water.
Simmer covered for about 30 minutes, or until lentils are tender.
Add rice and more water if necessary.
Look at the rice package for cooking time.
Once all water is absorbed, serve with fresh cornbread!

title: dinner rolls
directions: Optional:
Two eggs can be added, but will take more flour when kneading.

title: pecan candy
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add pecans.
Stir well until pecans are coated with mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull off bones.
Save stock and cook noodles. Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: salad supreme
directions: Prepare Jell-O; chill until mixture begins to jell.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Add pineapple to Jell-O mix and pur into oiled 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Chill until completely jelled.

title: lucky if any's left
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1 cup chopped pecans; mix well and put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix the softened cream cheese, sugar and 1 package Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with 1/3 cup orange juice and 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Pour over oranges and pineapple and let set overnight.
Before serving, add rest of ingredients.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Do not use stainless steel or any other type metal container!!!!!!

title: old-fashioned buckwheat cakes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients at night; stir well.
Cover and leave this in a warm place to rise.
Before breakfast, the sponge should be light and foamy.
Stir, then add the butter and soda, dissolved in water.
Beat well and pour from pitcher or tip of spoon to get a well rounded cake.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Makes 12 Buckwheat Cakes.

title: barley hot dish
directions: Cook barley for 1/2 hour and drain.
Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Add the green pepper and peas with liquid.
Add the tomato soup and paste with one can of water and the mushrooms. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the barley (cooked).
Mix all ingredients and bake in covered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and combine thoroughly. Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until set. The pie will make it's own crust as it cooks.
Serve at room temperature.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in 1/2 cup water for 2 to 3 minutes; add eggs and mix well.
Mix in ground beef, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and dash of pepper.
With wet hands, form meat mixture into small balls (about 24).
Put on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; turn meatballs and bake for another 10 minutes. Use with your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Can also use with a mushroom sauce.

title: apple devils
directions: Peel the apples.
Slice into eighths and remove core.
Place thin lemon slices on top of apples.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over all.
Add water.
Cover and cook on medium until barely tender. Uncover to finish cooking and thicken syrup a little, adding more sugar if desired.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking to pan and to cook uniformly.
Some or all of syrup will be absorbed as apples cool.
Good warm or cold.

title: maurice salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and refrigerate.
Serve over mixture of shredded lettuce, strips of ham, turkey, Swiss cheese and sweet gherkin pickles.

title: sugar-free rice krispie bars
directions: Put margarine, egg substitute and vanilla in saucepan and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from stove; cool slightly and add sweetener.
Stir in cereal.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Form into balls.
Yield:
50 balls; 26 calories each.
Diabetic Exchanges:
3 cookies equal 1 bread exchange.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients one at a time.
Stir well after each item. Place the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares or dip out.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in half of melted oleo.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil the margarine with the water and cocoa.
Mix the next 6 ingredients together; add into cocoa mix.
Beat until creamy. Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use a prepared chocolate icing.
Has a real chocolate taste and so simple to make.

title: huckleberry or blueberry pie
directions: Put oleo in pie pan and place in oven or microwave until melted.
Then remove and mix flour with melted oleo.
Spread evenly in pan and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Cool, then add on top the mixture of powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Put blueberry pie filling on top of this mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: jiffy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse in hot water.
Add bell pepper and onion.

title: beef roast
directions: Cover large roasting pan with enough foil to wrap roast in. Wash roast, salt and pepper one side.
Pour 1/2 of mushroom mixture in roaster.
Put roast in mixture, salted side down.
Pour rest of soup mixture on top of roast.
Salt and pepper this side.
Roll sides and ends of aluminum foil.
Cook in oven at 325° for 3 hours. Can be fixed the night before and cooked next morning (before going to church).

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Place meat in a large shallow glass dish. Combine soy sauce, sugar, lemon juice, brandy and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Pour over meat. Cover and chill for at least 6 hours, turning at least once. Remove meat.
Reserve marinade.
Grill over flame at medium setting 10 to 12 minutes on each side for rare, turning and brushing occasionally with marinade.
Cut across grain for serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beef, 3 ounces cheese and rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Place in a 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: tomato cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine meat, onion, bread crumbs, pepper, hot pepper sauce, catsup, garlic salt, seasoned salt and egg; mix until blended. Spread meat mixture over bottom of pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until meat is done.
Cut tomato in 1/2-inch slices; cut each slice in half crosswise.
Arrange around edge of pie when pie is about 1/2 done.
When pie is done, sprinkle tomatoes with grated cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: quiche
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain grease.
In a bowl, stir 4 eggs.
Add to eggs the beef and onion, Miracle Whip, milk, corn starch and cheese.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350.

title: hamburger and noodles casserole(good and easy)
directions: Brown meat with onions and butter. Drain off grease. Combine corn, water, soup and noodles with meat. Add salt and mix well. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender and mixture thickens. Stir occasionally while baking. Top with Mozzarella cheese last 15 minutes.

title: ranger crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, cream the margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs; beat until blended.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla. Mix all together until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by round teaspoonful.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: savory italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish. Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with half of the salad dressing; toss to coat well.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and wine to pan; sprinkle with remaining salad dressing.
Bake 25 minutes, basting chicken with drippings in pan occasionally, until juices run clear when pierced with fork and vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Put peaches over batter. Sprinkle with two tablespoons of sugar.
Pour juice over this and bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour the drained crushed pineapple; spread evenly.
Pour contents of pie filling evenly over crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle entire box of dry cake mix over pie filling; spread evenly.
Cut stick of butter into pats and place them over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Tastes great hot with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush cookies and mix with 1/4 c. margarine. Spread into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Pack down well. Freeze for 15 minutes. Take ice cream out of freezer to soften. Spread

ice cream on cookie mixture, and put in freezer. Bring to boil nest 5 ingredients and boil 1 minute. Cool. Mix in 1 c. spanish peanuts. Spread mixture on ice cream. Put cool whip on the morning you serve. Freeze, covered with foil.

title: candy coated pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark over low heat, stirring constantly.
Dip pretzels; place on wax paper and refrigerate until hard.

title: chocolate glaze for doughnuts
directions: Melt chocolate and butter or margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in confectioners' sugar and vanilla.
Mix in hot water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until glaze is proper consistency.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Stir and let set 20 minutes.
Add oranges and pineapple to cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients together. If using a cast-iron skillet, pour 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in skillet. Pour ingredients into skillet or pan. Spread some of the grease over top of the mixture. Place in oven and cook until golden brown.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
In pile, make 3 holes with a spoon.
In the largest hole, pour oil, next the vinegar and next the vanilla.
Cover holes after each addition. Cover with water and stir.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Add butter, milk and lemon juice. Stir well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50
minutes or until pie is set. Let cool on wire rack.

title: saucy pudding cake
directions: Beat 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and the softened margarine at medium speed until blended.
Stir together flour and next 5 ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with 1/2 cup water, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Recipe may be doubled.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 50 minutes.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu(with stuffing)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine broccoli, water, butter and vegetable seasoning packet in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in stuffing crumbs.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Place chicken breasts around edge of 12 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover each with slice of cheese and ham.
Spoon broccoli stuffing over ham.
Place remaining stuffing in dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Heat the gravy. Serve with chicken.

title: meal pie
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Stir together sugar and gelatin.
Blend egg yolks, water and lemon juice.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon peel.
Chill until mixture begins to mound slightly

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls in cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together and spread on cooled crust.
Put vegetables on top of crust, then sprinkle cheese on top of these.
Monterey Jack and Cheddar are nice together.

title: thanksgiving corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 325° or until the center of the dish is firm to the touch.

title: easy barbecue pork chops
directions: Combine Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Dip each pork chop in sauce, then sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of sugar on each side of the pork chops.
Marinate in sauce for 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake in preheated 325° to 350° oven.
After 30 minutes, turn pork chops and bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp canapes
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Top Escort cracker with a slice of white American cheese, a spoon of shrimp mixture and top with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: bruschetta
directions: Mix together tomatoes (chopped small) and onion and garlic, diced small.
Add dressing of oil, vinegar, basil and Italian seasoning.
Season to your taste.
Toast slices of Italian bread. Spread dressed tomato mixture over each slice.
Makes a wonderful hors d'oeuvre.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt and water in very large bowl or split between 2 bowls.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours, do not drain.
Add sugar and vinegar; stir until sugar dissolves.

title: pecan bread pudding
directions: Put egg white in glass measuring cup; add enough liquid egg substitute to make 1/2 cup.
Beat with wire whisk until mixture is well blended.
In large bowl, combine undiluted evaporated milk, nonfat milk, bread cubes and pecans; stir until all liquid is absorbed.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Then add apricot nectar, mix together and chill until it begins to thicken.
Add bananas, mandarin oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Pour into square or small rectangle Pyrex pan and chill until firm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in large bowl in order given.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Put on top of salad.
Let chill 24 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Beat eggs and gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add oil while beating.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon, stirring until smooth.
Stir in carrots; blend well.
Spoon mixture into prepared pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool slightly; turn onto racks to cool completely.
May be frozen.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Sift next 4 ingredients together; add alternately with sour cream to egg mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with vanilla or sour cream frosting.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Melt butter and saute green peppers and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2 qt. covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and bake 10 minutes more.
Melt Cheddar cheese on top and serve. Enjoy!

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased dish at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: If you are using pork steak, freeze it until firm and then slice it into very thin strips.
For ham, cut into long strips about 3/8-inch on a side.
Brown meat in frying pan or wok; use oil if necessary.
Drain pineapple juice from canned pineapple into a measuring cup and add water if necessary to get correct amount of liquid.
Add this to frypan or wok.
Stir in brown gravy mix, vinegar and ginger.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes, just until liquid begins to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in small balls and far apart on the cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 125 cookies.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Lightly butter 2 large cookie sheets (Pam may be used).
Do not use Teflon cookie sheets; it will ruin them.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart or larger saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in the butter. Stir frequently after mixture reaches the soft crack stage (270°). Add nuts; stir constantly until temperature reaches hard crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda, mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto cookie sheets.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Cook margarine, sugar, milk and egg first; boil 1 minute.
Cool off, then add 1 cup graham crackers, raisins, coconut and nuts.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: Sprinkle and swirl into cake.
Try not to touch sides of pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt until tender and then drain.
Melt cheese and butter, then add milk.
Add cheese sauce to broccoli. Mix in 3/4 of 1 package of crackers to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Stir in flour, cinnamon and soda.
Add pecans and mix well.
Line a cookie sheet with wax paper and press dough together, patting and shaping to a rectangle, approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
(A double batch usually covers the entire sheet.)

title: my surprise
directions: Combine ground chuck and cream of mushroom soup thoroughly. Spread out in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Layer the Tater Tots on the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roasts:  cook 'em plain and juicy
directions: Rub a light coat of salt over the meat; sprinkle with pepper. Place fat side up in a baking pan.
Put in a 325° oven for approximately 1/2 hour per pound of meat.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool, peel and coarsely shred.
In a saucepan, combine Cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup butter over low heat, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add shredded potatoes; stir gently and turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter; bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Butter cake pan (9 x 13); cover bottom with pieces of 1/2 of cake.
Beat butter, sugar and yolks together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 of mixture over cake pieces.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crushed candy bars, then repeat.
Chill overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Cover with rice, soup and mushrooms.
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Add oregano, garlic and spices to flour and mix.
Peel normal size eggplants and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Dip slices in slightly beaten eggs and then into seasoned flour.
Lightly brown the flour covered eggplant in hot oil in frying pan and let drain on paper towels.
(Reminder:
Remove paper towels before continuing.)
Place a layer of eggplant in the bottom of 9 x 18-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle over a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Place a second layer of eggplant and sprinkle over with Provolone cheese.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil for last ten (10) minutes until golden brown. Serves 12.

title: 1-2-3-4-5 salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: clam fritters
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine clams, egg, salt and pepper.
Add just enough flour to hold together.
Drop by large spoonfuls into hot oil in a skillet.
Panfry until golden on both sides.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Beat until well mixed.
Beat in 3 eggs, one at a time.
When well mixed, add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: linda's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter and add onion.
Cook until tender and add tomatoes, peas and drained mushrooms.
Cook and drain spaghetti and add to cheese.	Combine chicken and spaghetti with skillet mixture.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: savory sour cream spread
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
