Place cottage cheese and eggs in blender container; cover.
Blend on medium speed 30 seconds or until smooth, scraping down sides.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Add cottage cheese mixture, 1 1/3 cups of the sour cream and remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan; place on cookie sheet.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in lower third of oven until top just starts to brown. Turn oven off.
Leave pan in oven with door ajar 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool on wire rack.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need an 8-inch plastic flowerpot, small dirt scoop and cover from 12 ounce Cool Whip container.

title: pudding cake
directions: Make cake as directed; make pudding as directed.
Put layer of sliced bananas on top of cake.
Add layer of pudding.
Add layer of bananas.
Top all with Cool Whip.
Can use any fruit on pudding.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 2 strips of bacon. Sprinkle last 2 strips of crumbled bacon on top.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients into a batter. Brown meat and add onion and chilies. Sprinkle thin layer dry cornmeal in pan. Pour in half of batter, layer cheese, then layer meat mixture. Cover with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: a healthy cole slaw
directions: Finely chop broccoli and cauliflower by hand and place in medium sized bowl.
Add shredded lettuce to bowl.
Slice chilled pickles in quarters lengthwise and chop into small pieces.
Add mayonnaise (enough to coat) and toss ingredients together.
Chill for 10 minutes and serve.
A real healthy, crunchy change.
Serves 4.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Blend in flour. Add salt, pepper and liquid; mix well.
(If not enough liquid from mushrooms and beans, add enough water to make one cup.)
Add evaporated milk; blend.
Add beans and mushrooms; mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix the melted butter and crumbs; sprinkle over bean casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are browned.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown onion with shortening.
Add seasoning and chicken.
Add water (or chicken broth); cover and let simmer slowly until tender.
Remove chicken and add sour cream and flour (mixed) to drippings in pan.
Whisk well and bring to slow boil to thicken. Add chicken to sauce.
Serve with noodles or dumplings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and let cool.
Prepare instant jello as directed and allow to set up until almost firm.
After cake has cooled, take a knife and place slits on top of the cake. Pour the almost thickened jello over the cake and then place in refrigerator overnight.
Let frozen strawberries thaw and mix in Cool Whip and spread over the top of cake.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and chop.
Spread layer of chopped broccoli into baking pan.
Cover with cheese, soup (turkey and mayonnaise) which have been mixed together.
Cover with topping mixed with the margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients. Blend in vanilla, eggs, flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Line a baking sheet with wax paper.
Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar with hands to form a smooth dough. Shape into balls (small).
Place on wax paper.
Put in refrigerator.
In double boiler, melt chocolate bits and Crisco. When smooth, take peanut butter balls and insert a wooden pick. Dip in chocolate until 3/4 of ball is coated.
Return to wax paper, chocolate side down.
Refrigerate 30 or more minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together while keep adding sugar until desired sweetness. Mix together until creamy, then pour over cole slaw mix.

title: cheese tortellini salad
directions: In a LARGE bowl, mix cooked pasta with shrimp, artichokes, olives and peppers or pimentos.
Set aside.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter (oleo) in small saucepan.
Add chocolate and stir constantly (I melt in microwave) over very low heat until melted. Pour into small mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Chill until spreading consistency (12 to 18 minutes).
Fills and frosts 8-inch or 9-inch layer (2) cake or 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Thoroughly combine rice with all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Must stir after first 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together and add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and raisins or coconut or chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen medium-sized cookies.

title: strawberry cake(diabetic)
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Before you beat pudding, add dry jello.
Beat together.
Fold in Cool Whip, then fruit.
Pour over cake.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: corn bread for any time
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, meal, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl.
Stir in yogurt, oil and egg whites.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until light brown and a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Place pan on rack to cool. Leave corn bread uncovered overnight to dry out.
Cut in 1 inch cubes and store airtight at room temperature.
Can be frozen; use as needed.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, onions and soda.
Stir in buttermilk. Drop by spoon into hot cooking oil.
Deep fry until golden brown, about 2 minutes.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mash 1/2 blueberries; add to batter.
Add remaining berries, stirring by hand.
Sprinkle muffins with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in greased tins.

title: pineapple-lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Let set until syrupy.

title: crunchy green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to the package directions; drain and keep warm.
Heat soup and mushrooms until bubbly.
Lower heat and blend in sour cream.
Do not allow to boil.
Arrange green beans on serving dish.
Pour sauce over beans and top with onions. Serves 8.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour in bottom of glass dish.

title: hamburger harvest casserole
directions: Heat oven.
Combine chuck, onions, tomatoes, Worcestershire and salt.
Put into 1-inch layers in a 3-quart casserole.

Place in layers the potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and green pepper. Bake at 375°, covered, 45 minutes, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: no fat barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan and cook on low for 15 to 20 minutes or longer for a thicker sauce.
Brush chicken or other meat as it cooks; serve remaining sauce on side.
Serves 6. Contains 76 calories, 13 mg cholesterol and 0 grams fat.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove all drippings except 2 tablespoons.
Saute celery and green pepper in drippings until tender.

title: meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place one pie crust in pie dish and set aside.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add soup, 2 large tablespoons sour cream, potatoes and 1 to 2 handfuls of fried onion pieces, crumbled.
Mix together.
Tear cheese and fold in.
Cover with remaining crust.
Bake about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: "cool as a cucumber" salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, cucumbers, tomatoes and green onions.
Add dressing and eggs; toss gently until ingredients are evenly coated with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour in baking dish. Arrange bacon slices on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until juice has thickened.
A small amount of onion is optional.
Very good.

title: grand ole opry salad
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes the salt, pepper, water, vinegar, Wesson oil and sugar.
Stir; it may boil over. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna balls
directions: Mix together. Form into ball. Serve with crackers.

title: old fashion lemonade
directions: Wash and dry lemons.
Squeeze juice from lemons.
Combine sugar, 1 cup of water and the lemon skins.
Simmer, covered, 6 minutes.
Cool.
Squeeze out skins and discard.
Add lemon juice and remaining 4 cups water.
Serve well iced with lemon slice garnish.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: macaroon kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolk, almond extract and orange juice; beat well.
Combine baking powder, flour and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Stir in 3 cups coconut.
Cover dough and chill about 1 hour.

title: concession stand ham barbecue
directions: Cook ham and green pepper until heated very thoroughly. Separate ham as it cooks.
Drain juice. Add remaining ingredients to suit taste.
Makes approximately 45 sandwiches.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in an 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Serve with crackers.

title: shawn and reese's favorite banana birthday cake!
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour pans.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add banana puree; mix well.
Slowly add flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Fill pans; bake 30 to 35 minutes for layer cake (20 to 25 minutes for cupcakes and 35 to 40 minutes for sheet).
Cool, frost and decorate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Arrange sliced potatoes in a greased dish or pan.
Dot with butter.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour milk over this.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden brown or fork-tender.

title: **snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. With electric mixer at medium speed or "cream" or with spoon thoroughly mix shortening with 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until very light and fluffy.
At low speed or "blend" beat in flour mixture until batter is dough-like; chill until easy to handle.
Form dough into walnut-size balls; roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon, mixed.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine fine crumbs, confectioners sugar, 1 cup pecans and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll half in granulated sugar and remainder in 1/2 cup nuts.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well; add beaten eggs to mixture.
Put in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place layer of broccoli.
Combine rice, pimento, chicken soup, cheese sauce and chicken and spread over broccoli layer.
Place layer of noodles.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Heat until brown on top at 350°.

title: bean soup
directions: Blend soup and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: spicy apple twists
directions: Peel and core apples. Cut each into 8 wedges.
Open crescent rolls and cut the 8 triangles in half.
Wrap the 16 apple wedges with the dough.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Pour 3/4 cup water over apples.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over batter; do not stir. Place peaches on top of batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pickled peppers
directions: Boil water and vinegar with garlic.
Cut peppers in strips or quarters.
Place peppers in sterilized jars, pour vinegar mixture over peppers and seal.

title: german chocolate cake special
directions: Grease the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut and spread in the bottom of the pan.
Prepare the cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Spoon over the nut and coconut mixture.
In a sauce pan, heat margarine and cream cheese together and mix well.
Remove from heat and add 10 x sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon over top of cake batter.

title: cheese spread
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature.
Mix together.
Put in bowl greased with butter.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or bake as muffins for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese and nut salad
directions: Mash the cheese; moisten with cream and melted butter.
Season with salt and cayenne.
Add chopped nuts, pimento and olives. Press into a mold and let stand 2 hours.
Cut in slices and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise dressing.

title: macaroni medley
directions: Cook macaroni in salted, boiling water as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until soft, but do not brown.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, tomato sauce and water.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix olives and cheese with macaroni, saving out 1 cup cheese.

title: asparagus nut stir-fry
directions: In a skillet or wok, stir-fry asparagus in oil until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. Remove and keep warm.

title: oriental pork-vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Add remaining ingredients; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve hot.
Yield: 4 cups (65 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds and membranes.
Sprinkle insides of cups with salt.
Cook ground beef and onion until lightly browned.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce. Cover; simmer until rice is tender.
Stuff peppers; stand upright in a 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sumaki
directions: Stir the last 4 ingredients together until pancake batter consistency.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap water chestnuts in bacon; spear with toothpick (single layer) in a cake pan.
Pour mixture over to coat each Sumaki (not to cover whole pan).
Broil until crisp.
Serve hot.
May be reheated in microwave.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl cream butter.
Add cocoa and confectioners sugar alternately.
Add milk and blend in vanilla. Beat until desired consistency.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain beans and place in glass bowl.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over bean mixture; toss.
Refrigerate, covered, until served.
Drain before using.
Make night before.
Pimento may be used if desired.

title: grape pie
directions: Cook these together until thick, stirring occasionally.
It does not take long.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Do not worry if mixture seems to thin down at this point.
Add pecans and pineapple.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour or better overnight.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with whipped cream.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water. Add fruit. Refrigerate until mixture has cooled. Add sour cream, folding in thoroughly. Chill until firm.

title: easy and creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; wash and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz. Quick and easy meal for children.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Fold in coconut and gumdrops. Stir in oats until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 15 minutes).

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat milk and margarine over medium heat until melted and milk is scalded.
Mix remaining ingredients in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in milk mixture.
Place casserole in pan of very hot water (1 inch deep).
Bake until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Season with salt. Butter an 8 x 13-inch flat casserole dish.
Place layer of broccoli in dish.
Cover with mushroom soup and layer Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Repeat broccoli, mushroom soup and stuffing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Combine dry ingredients.
Puree banana in milk and oil.
Add nuts and process until chopped.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and stir.
Fill lined muffin tins with batter and bake 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, hamburger and onions until brown, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together with hamburger.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and spice or spices.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 3 big loaves.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all of above.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with 3 slices of bread (crumbled).
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies eggs
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter.
Once cooled, add sugar and Rice Krispies.
Form into egg shape and dip into melted chocolate. Let cool before serving.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion, milk and egg in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add next 4 ingredients; gently shape into balls by hand.
Melt Crisco in skillet.
Brown meat balls. Pour off grease.
Heat jelly and chili sauce in skillet; stir well until jelly is completely melted.
Add meat balls to sauce and stir until they are coated. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: rock cornish hens
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash hens and pat dry.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Rub lightly with oil.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss.
Stuff both hens equally and truss.
Place hens in uncovered roasting pan and roast for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with candied yams, buttered broccoli and cranberry salad.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Pop
popcorn.
Combine	and
bring to a boil the sugar, honey and
corn
syrup, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 1 minute. Remove
from
heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour	over popcorn
and mix well.
When cool, store in closed container.

title: frosting for sugar cookies
directions: In top of double boiler, heat and beat first three ingredients until frothy and chalk white.
Add marshmallows and beat until thick and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Clean beaters and beat some more.
Divide into sauce dishes and color; use immediately.
Cover when not in use.

title: watergate cake
directions: In large mixing
bowl put all ingredients at once.
Mix well, pour batter
into Bundt pan (greased and floured).	Bake at 325° for 55
to	60
minutes.
Cake is done when it springs back after being touched
in
the center.
Cool on rack for at least 15 minutes.
Glaze
or sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: oven-fried fish or chicken
directions: Mix crushed bread sticks with
garlic
powder and onion powder.
Dip fish or chicken
into
Butter Buds and then bread crumbs and place on a nonstick pan cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Recipe equals 1 protein unit, 1 grain.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice zucchini in half lengthwise. Scoop out the pulp from each half, leaving a shell a quarter-inch thick.
Brush outside of shells with oil and place in shallow baking dish.
Chop the pulp.
Saute garlic in oil for a few seconds.
Add chopped zucchini pulp and cook for one minute. Remove from heat and add bread crumbs, salt and 3 tablespoons grated cheese.
Mix thorougly.
Spoon mixture into zucchini shells.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: sour cream fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and stir well.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with fruits of your choice.

title: fresh apricot pie
directions: Double crust pie pastry, 1 egg beaten, 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Sprinkle lemon juice over fruit in large bowl.
Combine sugars, tapioca, salt and cinnamon, mix lightly with apricots.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, roll out half of pastry, fit in 9-inch pan.
Add apricot filling.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust.
Wet edge of bottom crust before placing top crust so it sticks together.
Flute edges.
Bake in 425° oven 45 minutes or until crust is brown and fruit is done.
May use peaches also.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Slice turkey breasts so they are half normal thickness. Season both sides with seasoning salt.
Mix picante sauce, Italian dressing, cilantro and pepper.
Cover the turkey, onions and green pepper with this mixture; refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: kjottkaker(norwegian meatballs, of course!)
directions: Place salmon skin side down on large piece of aluminum foil on a cookie sheet or flat pan, folding up edges of foil to collect juice.
Sprinkle fillet with wine, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Frost like a cake with mayonnaise (or combination of yogurt).
Decorate top with onion slices, then just before baking, sprinkle brown sugar over the top.
Bake, uncovered, on center shelf of oven, preheated to 400°, for 20 minutes only.
Serve immediately.
Do not overbake or fish will become dry.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix 2 cups of milk, sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until mixture boils and begins to thicken.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Cover giblets with water in pot.
Add bouillon cubes, onion, celery, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Boil, covered, for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup stock to drippings in turkey roaster.
Bring to boil, stirring well to loosen all brown bits from sides of pan.
Add 2 more cups giblet broth, stirring to blend.
Reduce heat.
Make a paste from flour and water until very smooth.
Add slowly to gravy mixture and continue to cook slowly, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove giblets and chop.
Add to gravy along with eggs.
Adjust seasonings.
If color of gravy is not dark enough, add up to 1 tablespoon "Kitchen Bouquet."
Yield:
5 cups.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly, draining off fat.
Add garlic, 1 1/2 tablespoons parsley, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Combine cottage cheese, remaining parsley, eggs, pepper and 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread half the cottage cheese mixture over them, then 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese over meat.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares. Makes 12 servings.

title: date swirls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat well.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix dates, lemon juice, water and sugar.
Cook together 5 minutes.
Add the chopped nuts to date mixture.
Spread over cookie dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper. Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: easy-quick chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips, cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, set aside.
Beat whole egg and two egg yolks until stiff. Add melted chocolate chips to eggs.
Fold in egg whites.
Whip whipping cream plus 1 tablespoon sugar until stiff.
Fold about 3/4 of whipped cream into chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Spread remaining cream on top.
Try a little creme de menthe in topping for a change.

title: western celery casserole
directions: Brown bread crumbs and almonds in oleo and set aside.
Cook celery in slightly salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Cover the bottom of greased baking dish with stuffing.
Add celery on top and add mushrooms on top of celery.
Cover with soup and milk mixed.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and almonds on top and cook 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Combine sour cream, soup and melted butter. Add salt, onion and cheese. Blend in hash browns. Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle corn flakes on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan in margarine, cook onion and celery until tender but not brown.
Blend in soup, cream and curry powder.
Add chicken or turkey, cooked rice, wine and parsley.
Put in 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can freeze.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a heavy skillet until onions and beef are soft and crumbly.
Add salt, rosemary, pepper, tomato paste, and water to beef mixture.
Mix well and simmer uncovered about 30 minutes.
In a shallow baking dish place enough sauce to cover the bottom, then 1/2 the noodles.
Spread with cottage cheese, thin slices of mozzarella, 1/2 of the remaining sauce, rest of the noodles, sauce, mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until it is bubbling hot.
Let stand before serving.

title: knox blocs (finger jello)
directions: Stir very well; pour into a long cake pan.
Place a piece of wax paper over top when you refrigerate.
(Great for sick kids.)

title: peanut butter rice krispies balls
directions: Put sugar and syrup in medium pot; bring to boiling point and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; beat until creamy.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until all cereal is mixed.
Spread on greased dish.
Cut into squares when cooled.
May also roll mixture into balls with damp hands.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and beat well the first 4 ingredients.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread mixture in greased and floured bread tins.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar, defrosted Cool Whip and drained pineapple in large mixing bowl.
Mix and beat until well blended.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat the cream cheese and mayo until smooth.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Cover and chill until firm.
Form into ball and roll in nuts to coat.

title: chicken rolls in phyllo
directions: Debone the chicken and chop
meat to make about 6 cups. Melt 1 stick butter
in
a
large	pot
and
cook onions for 5 minutes. Add celery;
cover	and
cook until tender.
Stir in chopped meat, broth,
salt
and
pepper;	cook until liquid is absorbed.	Remove from
heat	and
cool 10 minutes.
Beat eggs well and fold	into chicken mixture.
Add chopped parsley and nutmeg.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt remaining butter.

title: cherie's crazy chicken
directions: Lay chicken pieces in large flat casserole.
Mix well the cranberry sauce, French dressing and soup mix.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered and 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve over white rice.

title: very smooth cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling and pineapple in pan. Sprinkle pound cake mix over filling and pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over, then add coconut and pecans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When cool, serve with Cool Whip.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain.
Fry kielbasa; drain.
Cook macaroni as directed.
Stir everything together in 9 x 13-inch pan except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until everything is hot.
Top with cheese and return to oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine all but chocolate and paraffin.
Chill; roll into balls and chill again.
Dip into chocolate coating and chill.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, crumbs, egg, catsup, milk and seasonings. Mold into a rounded flat loaf in a 9-inch pie plate and spread catsup on top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High approximately 20 minutes or until done.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: california vegetables
directions: Mix and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Top with canned onion rings the last 10 minutes.
Easy on celery soup and don't overcook vegetables.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Cook 3 minutes and cool to lukewarm; soften 1 cake yeast in this mixture.
Add 3 1/2 cups white flour and mix to a soft dough; let rise 1 1/2 hours, then add 2 cups rye flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead dough lightly.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with a damp cloth and let rise until double.
Knead and divide into 2 pieces; cover and let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves; let rise.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
Brush tops with butter.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add and stir in brown sugar until dissolved. Add evaporated milk and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Continue beating until smooth. Double recipe for layer cake.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cheese until fluffy; gradually add Eagle Brand milk, beating until well blended.
Add lemon juice and blend in.
Pour mixture into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top.

title: fall harvest stew
directions: Saute meat, onions, peppers and garlic in olive oil and butter.
Add broth, wine, salt, pepper, bay leaf, thyme and tomato paste.
Cover; bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add squash, green beans, carrots, tomatoes and corn.
Bake an additional 45 minutes, then thicken broth.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt and drink mix.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend.
Add food coloring and vanilla.
Mix buttermilk, vinegar and soda.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: original recipe chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook vermicelli; drain.
Mix well with dressing and salad seasoning.
Toss well.
Mix in tomatoes and cucumber.
Store in refrigerator for several hours.
Turn bowl occasionally so dressing will mix through.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Saute onion and peppers in small amount of oil.
Mix together all ingredients with 1/2 the cheese.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread the mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the sour cream, onion and sauerkraut together and place in the casserole.
Layer the crumbled corned beef over the sauerkraut mixture, then lay the Swiss cheese slices over the corned beef.
Mix the melted butter with the rye bread crumbs and layer the bread crumb mixture over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix bread crumbs in loaf pan.
Beat eggs, sugar, butter, milk, vanilla, salt and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over bread crumbs in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood stew
directions: Add all ingredients except shrimp and cut seafood sticks. Cook until okra is done. Add shrimp and seafood.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: squash surprise
directions: Cook squash until done; take or peel spaghetti off, your (vegetable) spaghetti is ready.
Brown meat, onions and peppers until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Garlic powder to taste. Serve over spaghetti.
Low-fat!
Low calorie!

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour and sugar in 9-inch pie pan, using a fork.
Blend oil with milk.
Add mixture to dry ingredients in pie pan; mix with fork.
Press into shape.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes. Cool, then fill.

title: crab casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with the margarine, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat and stir.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until begins to thicken.
Add the other chopped ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, mushrooms and crab meat.
Stir well.
Put into a buttered baking dish and cover with 1/2-inch of buttered bread crumbs.
This is most important.
Bake at 350°
until brown, about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy mint punch
directions: In saucepan, combine water and jelly; cook and stir until jelly melts. Cool. In large punch bowl, combine jelly mixture with remaining ingredients except sherbet; mix well. Scoop sherbet on top of punch; serve immediately (stirring occasionally to keep mixture blended). Refrigerate leftovers.

title: garlic bread
directions: In a saucepan, warm up the olive oil and garlic with the salt and pepper.
Cut the bread as though you were going to slice it, only don't cut all the way down.
Now, spread the heated mixture in each slice.
Sprinkle on the paprika; wrap in foil the entire loaf.
Heat until hot enough, about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored and add to mixture.
Add flour, baking powder and salt to cream mixture, alternating with milk.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat eggs until light and add to mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients and add. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dessert salad
directions: Cut fruit in pieces.
Mix whipped cream and mayonnaise and pour over fruit.
Let stand overnight.

title: pickled watermelon balls
directions: Cut enough small balls from the red part of not quite ripe watermelon to make 8 pounds.
Put them in a saucepan and barely cover with cold water.
Cook until they are soft when pierced with a fork.
Drain and discard the water.

title: blue corn muffins
directions: Butter 12 (3/4-inch) muffin forms or line with paper liners. Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine egg, milk, oil and blue cornmeal.
Mix well, 8 to 10 minutes to soften cornmeal. In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
After meal mixture has rested, stir to re-mix and add to flour mixture. Stir, but gently, to combine.
Fill each cup 2/3 full. Bake 15 minutes or until brown.
Let pan cool for 3 minutes.
Turn muffins upside down and serve.

title: momma's lemonade pie
directions: Take frozen can lemonade out of freezer and let thaw approximately 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into large bowl and stir. Pour can of sweetened condensed milk in and stir together.
Fold in Cool Whip until fluffy.
Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then slice and serve.

title: jeff davis chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cream.
Beat eggs and add one at a time, then add juice of lemon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let stand few hours before serving. Refrigerate. Very good with chips or crackers.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cheese with butter; add remaining ingredients, folding in cereal last with hands.
Make into marble size balls, flatten with a fork and dash with paprika.
Bake on cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 50 to 60 wafers.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add beaten eggs, melted margarine, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla extract.
Stir in grated apples.
Let filling mixture stand.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa, sugar and milk in saucepan over high heat until oleo is melted.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon onto waxed paper or spread on cookie sheet.
Let set until cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute half of the chicken in 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Repeat with one tablespoon of oil and remaining chicken.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine buttermilk mix, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa. Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Stir in milk and vanilla until well blended.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/3 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Carefully pour hot water on top (do not stir). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked tuna-cheese buns
directions: Butter inside hamburger buns; set aside.
Combine all ingredients together.
Spoon mixture between buns; wrap in foil. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Bake wrapped buns at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: truck stop biscuits
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a bowl.
Mix in Crisco and buttermilk and form into a soft ball.
Place on a floured board. Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, then spread melted butter on top and bake 5 more minutes in oven temperature of 350°.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt.
Let bubble.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour.
Mix at high speed with mixer.
Add 2 cups more flour.
Use wooden spoon to mix rest of flour.
Let rise in icebox, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove and punch down.
This may be kept in icebox for 3 or 4 days.
Just take out as much as you need. Shape into rolls and let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° in oven until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Beat the eggs and mix lightly with drained and cooled squash.
Layer squash in a buttered casserole using
the crushed crackers and cheese. Dot top with oleo. Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes until brown.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion, butter, salt and pepper in skillet, but don't brown.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped cabbage over meat.
Then pour a 10 1/2 ounce can of tomato soup on top. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix the first 3 ingredients. Press mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
In large bowl, blend the eggs with brown sugar, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Add cherries, nuts and coconut.
Pour batter over baked crust; bake for 25 more minutes.
Cool and ice with frosting.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cheese and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple tidbits.
Spoon into greased casserole.

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in order listed.
Blend well. Pour into shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange tart shell
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, orange peel and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Gradually drizzle water over flour mixture, stirring and tossing with fork until dough cleans side of bowl and is not dry or crumbly.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface into 11-inch circle.
Carefully fit into 9 x 1-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Trim dough flush with rim of pan.
Gently pinch edges to stand about 1/16-inch above rim of pan.
Prick bottom of shell with a fork; place in freezer 5 minutes.
Line tart shell with aluminum foil; fill with dried beans or uncooked rice.
Bake in lower third of 425° oven for 8 minutes; remove beans and foil.
Continue baking 6 minutes or until bottom of tart shell is almost golden.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.

title: partridge with wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Place flour in a large resealable plastic bag.
Add birds and shake to coat.
In a large skillet, cook birds in oil until browned, remove.
Add milk and pepper to skillet, cook and stir until heated through.
Place the rice in a greased 9-inch square dish.
Top with birds and milk mixture.
Bake for 40-45 minutes or until a meat thermometer reads 180 degrees and meat is tender.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: pierogie casserole with kraut
directions: Mash potatoes with milk.
Saute onions in butter.
Add 1/3 of onion and butter mixture to 3/4 of cheese.
Add to potato mixture. Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place layer of noodles, layer of potato mixture and layer of sauerkraut.
Repeat, ending with noodles on top.
Pour remaining butter and onion mixture over top. Add remaining cheese.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt, eggs and vinegar.
Add coconut, nuts and raisins.
Pour into shells and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy caramels
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.

title: basic marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and use to marinate beef, pork or chicken.

title: latkes (potato pancakes)
directions: In a large bowl, combine thoroughly all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto hot griddle and fry until golden brown on both sides. Serve with applesauce and sour cream.

title: scott's chicken and gravy
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture and fry in margarine on medium heat in large skillet.
Cover skillet when frying on first side, uncover for second side.
Cook until golden brown, adding margarine as necessary.
Remove to platter; keep warm.
Add mushrooms to skillet, adding margarine as necessary.
Add cream to skillet.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour and cool water; mix with fork until smooth.
Add to cream and mushroom mixture, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Add bouillon to taste. Serve over rice or noodles and chicken.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large pan melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour the Crispix or Chex into melted mixture.
Mix enough to coat well, then let stand to cool.
In a brown paper bag, put powdered sugar and cooled mixture. Shake well. Store in plastic bag.
This is a great snack item that kids can make and enjoy. Great fun food!

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs for 1 minute at medium speed. Stir in buttermilk baking mix, cinnamon, raisins, nuts and dates. Pour into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, oil, vinegar and salt. Let cool. Pour over ingredients. Mix together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy roast chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Mix all soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes its own gravy.

title: tagine(moroccan chicken)
directions: Start lemons boiling in brine (salt water).
Mix oil, paprika, salt, cumin, saffron and pepper. Combine and brush over or dip chicken. Place, covered, in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour after adding water.
Add lemons plus olives, parsley, potatoes and artichokes. Bake 1 1/2 hours more, basting well.
Serve with French bread. (If you use fresh potatoes, be sure they are sitting in the liquid or they don't cook well.)

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Start with uncooked rice in bottom of long greased casserole. Pour combined ingredients over rice.
Place pork chops on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven 10 minutes before done.
Arrange pepper rings and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue cooking for 10 minutes more.

title: shredded apple pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done (about 50 to 55 minutes).

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Blend together the last 4 ingredients. Split rolls. Spread with margarine mixture on both split sides. Place the shredded ham and grated cheese on each roll. Put rolls together again.

title: icy tomato tune-up
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill well and serve or pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and freeze about 1 1/4 hours or until slushy.
Spoon into glasses.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Save 1/2 cup flour if needed later.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Then add sour cream and vanilla.
In another bowl mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix until combined. Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients.
Stir in center until mixed.
If still sticky add "saved" flour a little at a time. Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 350 degrees 10-12 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 - 6 dozen.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and condensed milk and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients to this mixture.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: heavenly pistachio
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts. Pack in a buttered 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Cool. Beat sugar and cream cheese together. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on top of baked and cooled crust. Beat pudding and milk. Spread on top. Let set; then top with Cool Whip and decorate with toasted coconut.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in bowl.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks and pineapple juice until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over fruit. Chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the potato chips. Cover mixture with crushed chips. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: allyson's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly together.
Chill.
Roll into ball. Serve with choice of crackers and chips.

title: special company breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and drain well.
Cube bread slices and place in bottom of ovenproof pan.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard and pour over bread cubes.
Spread sausage over top of eggs and then top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight and bake next morning in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry and line 9-inch pie plate.
Do not pierce pastry.
Prepare filling in a large bowl.
Beat eggs slightly; stir in sugar, salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Mix well. Stir in pecans and cranberries.
Pour fillig into pie crust. Cover edges of crust with foil to prevent overbrowning.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and butter in bowl over hot water; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: jam cake
directions: Grease and flour bottoms of three 8-inch pans.
Grind raisins, nuts and coconut in food processor.
Cream butter and sugar together; add vanilla.
Beat eggs and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix together with egg mixture.
Then fold in jam, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Pour into pans and bake 30 minutes or pick comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Add sugar to the persimmon pulp and also the beaten egg yolks. Stir. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Add to persimmon pulp mixture. Add vanilla, milk and margarine (melt margarine in pans and pour in leaving enough margarine in pans to grease the bottoms of two 9 x 13-inch pans).
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add to mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. This can be cut in half (only 1 pan instead of 2).
Can make a powdered sugar icing for topping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers, almonds and butter.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and almonds and slice butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain beans and save juice.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble. Layer beans, onion, bacon and almonds.
Add sugar and vinegar to bean juice.
Pour over beans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Thoroughly cream together the butter or margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with flat bottomed tumbler.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are delicately browned.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Dissolve well and pour over cucumbers, onions and green peppers.
Mix well and pack in jars or plastic containers.
Freeze.

title: boston cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, salt, cinnamon and soda with water mixture.
Stir in flour.
Add raisins and nuts. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Separate eggs (use whites in foolproof meringue).
Add 1/2 cup milk, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mixture while stirring to saucepan containing 1 3/4 cup scalded milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly until creamy.

title: chicken enchilada casserole(great for potlucks!)
directions: Bone chicken and chip into large pieces. Cut or tear into 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion and chilies together. Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish. Add 1 tablespoon juice from baked chicken in bottom of pan.
Place a layer of tortillas.
Add chicken and end with soups.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broc-burger
directions: Mix all ingredients well and grill.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Mix butter and garlic.
Spread over each slice of bread.
Cut each slice of bread in cubes.
Press into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with buttered sides down.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread evenly in dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours (or you may fix this recipe in the evening and let it refrigerate overnight).
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 1/4 hours. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings, 475 calories per serving.

title: broccoli and crab bisque soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onions, mushrooms, broccoli and garlic in butter until crisp.
Blend in flour, thyme, 1/8 teaspoon of salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add chicken broth and cream all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Add crabmeat; heat through.

title: cavatelli, cabbage and bacon(serves 6)
directions: Cook cavatelli according to package directions.
Drain and keep warm.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, fry bacon over medium-high heat until almost browned, about 5 minutes.

title: leftover ham, macaroni, cheese casserole
directions: In saucepan, lightly brown ham and onion in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (cover this to bake).

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place ingredients in 2-quart dish (with tight lid) in the following order:
uncooked rice, corn (drained), sprinkle salt and pepper; add 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water, onion, green pepper and uncooked ground beef.
Sprinkle salt and pepper; add 1 can tomato sauce and 1/4 can water.
Lay strips of bacon (cut in halves) over top.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour or until bacon is crisp.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Chill until firm enough to roll into a ball. Roll ball in chopped nuts until covered well.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Put margarine, oil, cocoa and water in saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar. Beat mixture well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, cinnamon, baking powder and eggs and beat well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar 3 times.
In separate bowl, put milk, melted shortening and eggs; beat slightly.
Blend into flour mixture.
Add raisins and caraway seed; mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: In microwave, bring brown sugar, oleo and syrup to a boil. Boil at full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in salt and soda.
Pour over popped popcorn in brown grocery bag. Close bag and shake well.
Microwave in bag at full power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake well.
Return to microwave and cook another 1 1/2 minutes; shake again and cook for third time for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into a shallow pan and cool.

title: potato casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes in jackets with bay leaf in boiling salted water until barely tender.
Cool, peel and grate.
Add butter to soup.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, salt, pepper, green onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix gently until blended.
Spoon onto casserole. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining cheese with cornflake crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in the pineapple and spread around the pan.
Spread the cherries on top of the pineapple; then sprinkle the dry cake mix over the fruit.
Add the nuts and place squares of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: white macadamia nut cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat the shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add about half of the flour, the brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat mixture until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate pieces and, if desired, nuts. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: sweet potato pie(daddy's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Do not drain liquid from yams.
Combine all ingredients, except crust.
Using either a mixer or blender, mix until rather creamy and smooth.

title: banana breeze pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and blend. Add 1/3 c. lemon juice, vanilla and stir until thickened.
Slice 3 bananas and line crust.
Pour filling into crust and refrigerated hours.
Slice remaining bananas, dip in lemon juice and use as garnish.

title: b.l.t. bites
directions: Cut a thin slice off of each tomato top.
Scoop out and discard pulp.
Invert the tomatoes on a paper towel to drain.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into tomatoes.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve peach gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and mix well.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in sliced peaches and banana.
Pour into lightly oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, yeast into large mixing bowl.
Let set 5-10 minutes until bubbles form.
Add eggs, butter, salt.
Then add flour gradually stirring with wooden spoon.
When too thick to stir add flour in small mounts, kneading until a soft dough and elastic. Let rise until double (about one hour).
Punch down and divide into pieces and let set covered 10 minutes.
Roll into triangles.
Brush on butter and sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Roll into jelly roll, cut into 3/4 inch to one inch pieces.
Place into cake pan or greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until good and brown.
Brush on frosting/glaze while hot so it melts.
Can be frozen.
To warm up heat oven to 350° and turn off.
Put in rolls for 30 minutes.
They will be just like fresh baked.
Makes about 45 rolls.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs, peel and cut eggs in half.
Put yolks in a bowl and mix in pureed asparagus, onions and mayonnaise.
Blend until smooth.
Put mixture in decorator tube and squeeze into white of boiled eggs.
Refrigerate until serving.
Season to taste.

title: summer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except yogurt. Stir in yogurt.
Serve chilled.

title: picante onion soup
directions: Cook onions and garlic in butter in saucepan until onions are tender. Add tomato juice, broth and water; simmer for 30 minutes. Add cheese and croutons to your bowl of soup.

title: homemade custard
directions: Baking time: 3/4 to 1 hour.
Temperature: 375°.
Size pan: casserole dish.

title: oreo dream
directions: Crush Oreos in	bottom	of dish.
Layer with thawed ice cream. Seal with Cool
Whip.
Freeze 1 hour or more and serve with chocolate sauce.

title: boiled rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling water and cook until tender.
Then put sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla into blender and beat well.
Add this to boiled rice and mix until it starts or comes to a boil, then cover and let stand.
If it boils too much, it will be watery.

title: creme sicle slush
directions: Blend with mixer until smooth and then freeze.
Use 7-Up mixed in glass.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place foil in center of baking pan. Spread butter on foil. Cut steak into serving size portions. Arrange on foil. Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, & green pepper.

title: mom's e-z green bean casserole
directions: Take 2 cans green beans.
Drain and spread out in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Spoon over green beans.
Take 1 package crackers.
Crumble in hand.
Cover over top of mixture.
Place in oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cherry almond coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1-1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well. In a small saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until very warm (not boiling) 120-130°. Add warm liquid and eggs to flour mixture. Blend at low speed until moistened; beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. By hand, stir in additional 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour to make a stiff batter. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: frito salad
directions: Chop lettuce into large mixing bowl.
Add tomato, bell pepper, onion, beans and cheese.
Just before serving, mix in Catalina dressing and last of all, the Fritos.

title: imo lou evans's citron preserves
directions: Peel melon and remove seeds.
Bring sugar and water to a boil and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Drop in citron slices and simmer until transparent.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Add ginger.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Mix in 1 1/2 qt. saucepan the sugar, milk and butter.
Cook stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil.
Boil and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
With 2 teaspoons, drop quickly onto wax paper. Let stand until set.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: frypan pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in large, iron frypan.
Add brown sugar and stir until smooth and even.
Arrange maraschino cherries, spoon on crushed pineapple evenly.
Mix cake mix according to directions, using pineapple juice for liquid.
Pour into frypan on top of pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Invert on plate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, stirring until cooked 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in water, chicken base, broccoli, salt, nutmeg and red pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Drop heat to medium, boil about 7 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Add the half and half.
Mix well.

title: microwave acorn squash with cranberry filling
directions: Wash and dry squash.
Place in microwave oven.
Heat, uncovered, on full power 15 minutes or until they feel soft to the touch.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side up in a shallow heat-resistant nonmetallic baking dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Place 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon honey in each half.
Heat, uncovered, on full power 4 minutes or until butter has melted.
With brush or spoon, spread honey-butter mixture over cut surfaces of squash.
Place a spoonful of cranberry sauce in each squash half.
Can be returned to reheat on full power 6 minutes or until cranberry sauce is hot.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt; add to egg mixture.
Dissolve soda in hot water; add soda water, nuts and dates to batter.
Beat.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen cookies.
When cool, ice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Mix in whipped cream.
Put in chocolate pie crust or graham cracker crust; then freeze.

title: snickers
directions: Combine (by hand) cake mix, nuts, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Divide batter in half.
Put half of the batter in greased pan.
Bake at 300° for six minutes.
While baking above mixture, melt caramels with remaining 1/3 cup milk.
When six minutes are up, remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top, then add caramel mixture and then the remaining batter.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: potato latkes
directions: Peel and shred potatoes (2 cups).
Place potatoes in colander; press down to extract as much liquid as possible.
In medium bowl, lightly beat eggs with onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper and the potatoes.
In large skillet, heat 1/2-inch oil to 350°.
Spoon tablespoon of potato mixture into hot oil, a few inches apart.
Flatten each to about 2 1/2-inch circle.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 200° oven.
Serve with desired topping.

title: hush puppies
directions: In deep saucepan, heat oil to 375°.
In mixing bowl, mix cornmeal, milk and egg until blended well.
Stir in onion.
Drop, a few at a time, by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Fry for 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 20.

title: rice pudding (custard)
directions: Mix the rice and raisins in the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over the top of the rice and raisins.
Place baking dish in a shallow pan of water and bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes and in a 375° oven for the rest of the baking time (about 1 hour total).
Test like custard with a knife for doneness.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix batter and pour over melted butter (do not mix). Pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken until done.
Pour spaghetti sauce into a casserole dish; add chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of chicken.
Add Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake for 15 minutes or until top is lightly brown.

title: snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add salt and flour; mix.
Add vanilla and fold in chopped nuts.
Make small balls, using about one teaspoon mixture.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes. While still warm, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: princess cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together with an electric mixer. Add eggs, mixing well, followed by vanilla extract. In a separate bowl, combine oats, flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture in several additions. Stir in dried cherries and white chocolate chunks. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets 1-inch apart. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef over medium heat.
Stir in onion and cook down until meat is brown.
Drain any excess grease, but reserve (you may need it later).
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add salt, if needed.
If mixture tastes flat, add a little of reserved drippings from ground meat.
Serve on hamburger buns and enjoy!

title: chicken stew with parsley dumplings
directions: Heat chicken, 4 cups water, onion, bouillon and pepper to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven pan; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered 30 minutes.
Add carrots; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir mixture and celery into chicken mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix baking mix, milk and parsley until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling stew.
Cook, uncovered over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make and chill 24 hours before serving.

title: take n' bake casserole
directions: Combine 3/4 cup American cheese, chicken, pimento, Romano cheese and pepper. Cook mushrooms and onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Toss lightly with chicken mixture.
Put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining American cheese. Cover securely. Keep chilled until baking time.
Just before baking, pour milk over.
Sprinkle crumbs that have been lightly browned in tablespoon of butter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add the Jell-O. When it begins to set, pour over the sliced berries that have been arranged in a prebaked pie shell.
Top with the whipped cream.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings. Mix flour and salt; stir into shortening mixture.
Divide dough in half and blend food coloring into 1/2.
Roll a 4 inch strip (1 tablespoon) dough from each color in flour.
Place strips side by side; press lightly together and twist like rope.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Form in shape of cane.
Bake 9 minutes until lightly browned.
While still warm, sprinkle with mixture of candy and sugar.
Makes 4 dozen canes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1 cup of rice on bottom of a dish. Put all soup on top of rice; place cut-up chicken into the dish. Top chicken with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered for 2 hours.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Pour half in dish and put in refrigerator until firm.
Leave other half out of refrigerator until ready to use.

title: sonnenberg apple salad
directions: Chop walnuts and apples; mix in bowl.
Add raisins, mayonnaise and beer.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for 2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: best ever egg nog
directions: Pour egg nog mix over ice cream. Whip until frothy. Fold in whiskey to taste. Place in freezer 1 hour, then serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and put in bag.
Shake biscuits in sugar mixture and place in tube pan.
Pour pecans between sugar-coated biscuits.
Combine brown sugar and butter; heat until melted.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° until brown.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Boil pudding mixes, sugar and canned milk 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla.
Whip until creamy.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Eat!

title: southwestern stuffed peppers
directions: Stem and seed pepper halves.
Cook in boiling salted water for 3 minutes; drain.
Place cut side up in shallow baking dish. Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet. Add tomatoes, water, barbecue sauce and salt.
Bring to a boil. Stir in pasta; reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix in corn.
Spoon mixture into pepper halves.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut
broccoli
and
cauliflower flowerets into bite size pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.

title: great pear pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in unbaked pie crust.
Mix next 3 ingredients and crumble on top of pie.
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour.

title: double chocolate chip cookies(i've received a lot of compliments on these cookies.)
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in eggs.
Add flour and mix.
Add chips and mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Cream until there are no lumps.
Pour in condensed milk.
Use mixer and stir well. Make pudding as directed.
Add to condensed milk and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour or spoon over layers of wafers and bananas.
Can be frozen.
This makes a large quantity and requires large containers for mixing.

title: holiday sausages
directions: Cook tiny pig sausages in dry white wine to cover, simmering them gently for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour off the wine.
Roll the sausages in biscuit dough, pinching the edges to seal in.
Arrange in a buttered baking dish; brush them well with melted butter. Bake at 400° until crisp and brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chile corn dip
directions: Combine the Mexicorn, sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese, green chiles, jalapenos, green onions and sugar in a bowl and mix well. Chill, covered, for several hours to allow the flavors to blend. Serve with large corn chips.
Yields 24 servings.

title: oatmeal marble squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: ham and cheese cornbread rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites, applesauce and cheese.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes. Carefully turn out onto clean towel.
Start at wide end and roll up with towel.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.
Unroll and top with ham slices.
Mix mayo and mustard.
Spread over ham.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Re-roll.
Place seam side down in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cut in 10 slices.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer all ingredients into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable calzone
directions: Thaw dough and let rise per package directions.
Combine broccoli,
Ricotta, Mozzarella, garlic and pepper in a bowl. Punch down and divide bread dough into 4 parts and roll on floured surface into 4 (8-inch) circles.
Place 3/4 cup cheese mixture onto half of circle, leaving 1-inch border.
Fold over, press and crimp edges with a fork to seal.
Brush with egg.

title: grandmothers tomato sauce
directions: Peel
and chop vegetables. Add vinegar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours. Put into jars immediately. Process in water.

title: whole wheat oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir dry ingredients together (except oatmeal) and
add to sugar/egg mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins, if desired.
Drop onto cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: banana-nut bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine;
add egg yolks and mix well. Add banana.
Sift
dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream to
margarine
mixture.
Mix
thoroughly.
Add vanilla, stiffly beaten
egg whites and nuts.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at
for 1 hour.
When cool, cut into bars and dust with powdered sugar.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk; mix thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into a greased 9 X 13 pan.
Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes.
Dot with oleo. Bake uncovered at 350 for 50 minutes.

title: cinnamon twist rolls
directions: In
large
bowl
thoroughly
mix 2 cups flour, 2 tablespoons sugar,
salt
and
yeast
(undissolved).
Combine sour cream, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat
2 minutes
at
medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and rest of flour.
Stir to make a
soft dough.
Turn
out onto lightly floured board, knead a few
times to
form
a ball.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Divide
dough in
half.
Roll
out
each
half into a 12-inch square.
Brush lightly with margarine.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and
teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle
center
third
of each square
with
3 tablespoons
of sugar mixture (also pecans or coconut
if
you wish).
Fold 1/3 of dough over center third. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of sugar mixture.
Fold remaining third of
dough over
the
layers.
Cut into strips about 1-inch wide.
Take hold
of
each
end of strip and twist tightly in opposite direction;
arrange in 2 greased 9-inch square pans. Brush
with margarine and let rise.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
When done, brush with margarine and cool.
Frost with confectioners sugar
icing.
Combine
about 2 cups sugar with enough water to make it spread.

title: lemon flavored pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
In separate bowl, combine flour and next 6 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine pumpkin and rum.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with pumpkin mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack and let cool completely on wire rack.
Delicious with cream cheese icing or delicious without icing.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Brown ground chuck.
Rinse to drain off fat.
Add onion and bacon.
Cook until onion is tender.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and mustard. Add kidney beans, butter beans and baked beans.
Mix together with bacon, onion and ground chuck.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange-cranberry
directions: Put all in food processor.
Grate orange on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered casserole dish. Mix together other ingredients and sprinkle evenly over apples.
Place in oven at 350° and bake until bubbly brown.
May be
served hot or cold. (Be sure to maintain temperature when transporting; keep either hot or cold.)

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Marshmallow Creme and margarine.
After it strikes a hard boil, let boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in pan. Makes 5 pounds.

title: bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large Dutch oven and bring to boil. Soup is ready when it is warmed through.
This may be used in a crock-pot, but use 1 cup water.

title: cherry chiffon gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Divide jello mixture into 2 equal parts.
After jello starts to thicken, add Bing cherries to 1/2 of the mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; let set.
Fold whipped topping into other 1/2 of jello mixture.
Pour this over fruited layer after it has set.
Refrigerate overnight until completely set.
Serves 24.

title: cwikta or beet sauce
directions: Bake or pressure-cook beets.
It seems that baking or cooking quickly under pressure preserves the redness of the beets better than a long boiling process.
Peel and grate the beets and mix with horseradish.
Add salt.
Cover with vinegar and keep cold in a jar.
Serve with cold meats or boiled meats.
(This is served at Easter and excellent accompaniment to fresh sausage.)

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chicken broth may be made by dissolving 2 bouillon cubes in 1 1/4 cups of water.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, in buttered casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 35 minutes longer or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: micro golden omelet
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Set aside. Microwave browning dish on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and allow to melt.
Pour egg mixture into dish.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until set, but still moist.

title: country fried steak
directions: Have your grocer run the round steak through the tenderizer or you can beat it on each side with the edge of a saucer.

title: that good rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine and saute onion. Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add rice to onion and butter.
Mix in juice from both lemons and sour cream.
Mix well and it's ready.
Goes great with broiled chicken.

title: pineapple punch
directions: In bowl of food processor, combine all the ingredients. Process for 30 seconds until finely ground.
Transfer to a tightly sealed container; label and date.
Store in a cool, dark place for up to 3 months.

title: chicken wing pacifica
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in soy sauce, brown sugar, water and mustard.
Arrange chicken wings in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour in butter sauce, turning chicken to coat, thoroughly.
Cover and chill 2 hours or longer.

title: green salad
directions: Let jello set until jelled.
Beat.
Add soft cream cheese, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Keep refrigerated until it sets again.

title: cherry squares
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, nuts and dry ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Spread 2/3 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherries over batter.
Spread the rest of the batter into 5 little patches; patches will spread while baking.

title: crab chowder
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter.
Add cooked potatoes, soups, crabmeat and milks.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours or in a crock-pot.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: In small bowl, mix well both the flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
With finger, work in the margarine until dough begins to hold together.
