Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan. Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until firm.
In medium bowl, lightly beat 1/2 cup brown sugar and eggs; add corn syrup, pecans, melted margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over crust. Bake 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.

title: yummy rum balls
directions: Combine rum, crushed wafers, light syrup and nuts.
Roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: health candy
directions: Heat honey and peanut butter until soft.
Mix in other items. Spread in greased pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hurry-up fruit salad
directions: Empty one large can of fruit cocktail with juice in a serving bowl.
Empty one small can of mandarin oranges (drained) into same bowl.
Take small package of instant pudding (either vanilla, lemon, coconut or banana) and empty the dry powdered pudding into bowl and stir contents.
(Do not prepare the pudding; use it only as a powdered substance.)
Refrigerate few minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onion in the butter in pan until clear. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir into sauteed mixture and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in a large baking dish and bake for approximately 35 minutes.

title: mother royer's white sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over "Mother Royer's English Christmas Pudding."

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in oil until soft. Add to rest of ingredients in a large pan. Cook until tortellini floats.

title: potatoes sausage casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Layer potatoes in bottom, 1/2 of soup mixture next, 1/2 of sausage; repeat, ending with sausage.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven 2 to 3 minutes, uncovered.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Place in a Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pesto
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine garlic, basil, pine nuts and salt.
Blend at low speed until ingredients are chopped fine and form a paste.
Gradually blend in oil alternately with cheese, blending until well mixed.
Store in a jar and cover with a layer of olive oil.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine chicken soup, sour cream and margarine.
Add potatoes, onion, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, cornstarch, sugar and hot water.
Cook until thickened.
Place sliced strawberries in cooked pie shells.
Pour thickened mixture over strawberries.
Place in refrigerator and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pies and place some berries on top.

title: moses' no bake cookies
directions: In large skillet, boil butter or margarine, sugar and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until dissolved; stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to set.

title: fish in a pouch
directions: Tear large enough piece of foil to envelope fish.
Place fish on foil.
Top with tomatoes, green peppers, onion, garlic, pepper and dill weed.
Place foil pouch on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook, drain and mash carrots.
Add remaining ingredients, putting eggs in last.
Mix well.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole dish and then in pan with 1-inch of water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock roast beef and vegetables
directions: Trim any fat from roast and sear all surfaces until very dark. Brown in medium-hot to hot frying pan.
Peel and cut carrots in serving size pieces and arrange in bottom of crock-pot.
Cover carrots with water or liquid of your choice.
Add onion wedges and potatoes.
Cut in half or quarters.
Top with roast.
Start the crock-pot on high for 15 to 30 minutes.
Cook on low for 8 hours or longer.
(Could even be started the night before; just leave the crock-pot on low.)
Remove roast and vegetables to platter or platter and serving bowl.
Turn crock-pot to high and scrape browned vegetables and meat from sides into liquid.
If liquid hasn't come to boil, pour it into saucepan to heat for gravy.
In small bowl, stir 3 or 4 tablespoons of cornstarch into about 1/2 cup cool water.
When liquid is boiling, stir while pouring cornstarch mixture into pan.
If gravy seems thick enough, stop adding cornstarch.
Season gravy to taste.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix together the orange slices, dates, coconut and nuts, set aside.
In mixing bowl cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Combine the flour and soda, add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
When mixed well fold into the first mixture. Grease and flour bundt pan, or spray with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or bake in 3 two lb. loaf pans.
Check loaf pans after 1-1/2 hours with a toothpick to see if they are done.

title: upside-down ravioli
directions: Brown onions, garlic and ground chuck.
Add tomato sauce and paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Cook spinach and let cool; add parsley and beaten eggs.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix together and stir.
Place in greased casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered. Serves 10 to 15.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa; cool.
Blend flour and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add cooled mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan, 10 1/2 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (do not overbake).
While cake is still warm, spread Marshmallow Creme over top.
When cool, spread with icing.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening and brown sugar together until crumbly. Set aside 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
Mix warm water, soda, baking molasses and salt by hand (no mixer).
Mix crumbs to molasses mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle the cup of crumbs over the top of the cake mix before baking.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Stir in raisins and oatmeal.
Mix well and stir in applesauce.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Prepare all veggies; place in large bowl with seal (like Tupperware or Rubbermaid).
Combine vinegar, vegetable oil, lemon juice, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper into shaker container. Shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight, stirring occasionally.
Makes a bunch!!

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter and add onions, garlic, celery and bell peppers. Simmer until onions turn yellow.
Add tomato sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add green onions, thyme, basil and shrimp; cook for 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Then top with a sprinkle of fresh parsley.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: lemon delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Add flour, butter and 1/2 cup nuts in mixer until it's in a ball; then press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn, meat and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt, chili powder and paprika.
Mix in Niblets, tomato sauce and noodles.
Pour all ingredients into casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in oven to brown, about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cheesy corn chowder
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in prepared pan.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix shortening, sugars and evaporated milk.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and vanilla, then add powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, oatmeal, Alba, and sweetener; and add as much water as needed to form a soft ball.
Chill. Serves 1.
1 serving equals 1 bread, 1/3 c. milk, 1 protein, and 1 fat.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour and Crisco with fork.
Add egg, salt and water.
Mix and divide into 3 balls, roll out each ball very thin and let dry for 20 minutes.
Cut into small strips and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Debone and break into hunks.
Mix soup, sour cream, poppy seed and chicken.
Put in a casserole dish.
Mix margarine and crackers and place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg and bacon breakfast
directions: Blend in blender oleo, mustard, eggs, milk, salt.
Combine bread, bacon and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixture from blender to refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: date bars
directions: Mix flour sifted with baking powder.
Add dates and nuts. Beat egg yolks; add sugar, combine with flour and fruit.
Fold in whites of eggs well beaten.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Wash and pare potatoes; cut each into 4 thick slices.
Dip slices in butter and arrange in shallow baking pan.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil; continue to bake about 30 minutes or until delicately brown, turning once. Sprinkle with salt.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Stir-fry beef in skillet until brown.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Mix broth and cornstarch; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil, then boil 1 minute.
Prepare rice as directed.
Serve beef over rice. Approximate cooking time:
30 minutes.

title: norfolk pudding(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Wash the rice well and cook in the milk, using a double saucepan if one is available.
Chop the suet and peel finely; add to the rice with peel, currants and sultanas.
Add the sugar, nutmeg and salt and beat all together thoroughly.
Put into a well-greased pie-dish and bake in a slow oven for a few minutes. (WCB)

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasoning, soup, beans and salsa.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 2 shells on bottom.
Add 1/2 of mixture and cheese.
Layer 2 more shells.
Add rest of mixture.
Top with 2 more shells and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold cranberry sauce, celery and nuts into gelatin mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled 2-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Melt the chocolate chips and pour over the peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove and slice into squares.
Leave in pan and put back in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: In a saucepan, melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside. In a separate saucepan, melt margarine and 1/2 cup evaporated milk; set aside. Mix dry cake mix and nuts together. Add to margarine mixture. Press half of this dough into bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on hot crust. Drizzle caramel mixture over crust. Press on remaining cake dough. Bake in a 350° oven for 18 minutes. Cool slightly. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut into 24 squares. (Tastes better if kept refrigerated.)

title: yummy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato soup, together; mold into balls the size of golf balls.
Pile into well oiled casserole dish.
Pour 1 can tomato soup over all.
Thin the tomato soup first with 1/3 cup water.
Bake slowly for 2 hours at 300°. Remove lid after 1 1/2 hours (or bake at 375° for 1 hour).

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Place
chicken	in
pot;
add
water and the 2 teaspoons salt. Bring
to boil;
cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove
chicken
from
broth
and cool covered. Bone chicken
and
cut into pieces; set aside.
Combine flour, soda and
1/2 teaspoon salt; cut in shortening until resembles corn meal.
Add buttermilk.
Stir.
Turn onto floured surface; knead 4 to	5
times.
Pat	to
1/2 inch thickness.
Pinch off dough in
inch	pieces and drop into boiling broth into which
pepper has been added.
Reduce heat to medium low.
Cook 8 to
10 minutes,
stirring a few times. Add chicken and stir. Yield 4 to 6 servings.

title: cinnamon bears
directions: You will need cookie cutters (bears or any favorite cutter).

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla and beat until thick.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point. Add to mixture.
Bake in buttered pan (8 x 8-inch) in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost. Return to hot oven or broiler to brown.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and chicken in margarine until meat is white
on both sides.
Stir
in
soup,
salt
and
pepper. Simmer 1 hour with 14 coals on top and 14 coals on the bottom. Add dry stuffing and cook 10 minutes and then serve.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add all ingredients by layers as listed.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into small squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler or in microwave.
Add noodles and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until set.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Using cake mix, make 2 round chocolate layers.
Split each one, giving you 4 layers.
Put first layer of cake on plate.
Sprinkle with Kahlua.
Spread Cool Whip on cake.
Sprinkle with broken toffee bars.
Repeat with other 3 layers finishing with a layer of Cool Whip and a generous helping of toffee bits.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add all other ingredients, except apples.
Mix thoroughly.
Dip slices of apples and enjoy!

title: country apple pie
directions: Line uncooked pie shell with thinly sliced apples.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and cream and pour over apples.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon mixed together over the top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix flour with salt and cocoa and dissolve soda in buttermilk. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour or until done.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions in large pieces.
Slice jalapenos. Mix together the sugar and vinegar to dissolve sugar in a large kettle.
Add tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Bring to a boil. Put hot mixture in canning jars and water bath for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini-corn-chile-cheese
directions: In a large frying pan, add 1/4 cup butter and the 2 medium zucchini cut up in disks and saut.

Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook until softened and brown. Next, add 2 cups corn, cover with a lid and cook until corn is soft. The last thing to do is add the slices of cheese and chili. Let this melt together. Cook over medium heat and the whole thing takes about 20 minutes to cook.

title: good punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a gallon jar. Finish filling jar with water. Chill. Serve with ice ring or ice cubes.

title: crock-pot pumpkin spiced stew
directions: In skillet, heat oil; saute onion, garlic and green pepper. Cook until pepper is softened.
Place in crock-pot; add zucchini, tomatoes and juice and pumpkin.
Sprinkle spices on top.
Cook on high in crock-pot 3 hours.
Serve hot with grated Cheddar cheese on top of each serving.
Serves 6. Serve with crackers.

title: rouladen
directions: Tenderize steaks with mallet.
Brown bacon; drain and crumble. Saute onions and mushrooms in a little margarine.
Add crumbled bacon; set aside.
Spread mustard heavily on one side of steak with salt and pepper.
Spread onion mixture on steak.
Roll up and fasten with thread.
Roll in flour; brown on all sides with margarine and add hot water for gravy.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until done; thicken gravy with cornstarch, dissolved in cold water.

title: hamburger italiano
directions: In hot butter, saute onion and green pepper 5 minutes.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add beef mixture, mushrooms, tomato soup and chopped tomato.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes.
Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until nicely browned.

title: syrup cookies
directions: Mix in order:
eggs, sugar, syrup, Wesson oil, flour, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
In juice, put onion and pepper and cook for a while, then add rest of ingredients.
Better to make the day before.
You can add a little water instead of all catsup.

title: nut pecan crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients until well coated.
Drop nuts, one at a time, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Keep loose.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and place in a casserole dish.
Mix egg, mayonnaise, chicken soup, cheese and rice together; pour over broccoli.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix and cover over this with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Disjoint chicken and season.
Beat egg lightly; add cream. Roll chicken in this mixture and then in flour.
Fry in deep oil (not too hot) until golden brown, or tender.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, peanut butter and salt.
Then add dry ingredients. Put by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 minutes at 325°. (Watch last 3 minutes.)

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix. Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll 1-inch ball and roll in sugar. Flatten with fork.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Pour into a 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in pineapple, bananas, nuts, Cool Whip and strawberries. Mix lightly and freeze overnight.
Serve a couple of hours later, taking out of freezer.

title: salmon baked in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle the salmon with 2 teaspoons oil.
Salt and pepper.
Stir the tomatoes, shallots, 2 tablespoons oil, lemon juice, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper in a medium bowl to blend.
Place salmon fillet, oiled side down, on top a sheet of foil.
Wrap the ends of the foil to form a spiral shape.
Spoon the tomato mixture over the salmon.
Fold the sides of the foil over the fish and tomato mixture, covering completely.
Seal the packets closed.
Place the foil packets on cooking sheet.
Bake until the salmon is just cooked through, about 25 minutes.
Using a large metal spatula, transfer the foil packets to plates and serve.

title: fat-free baked chicken breasts
directions: Skin breasts and salt.
Mix milk and beaten egg together. Crush corn flakes thoroughly, then shake 1 piece of chicken at a time in them, coating the chicken well.
Arrange pieces in a long baking dish; place in the oven at 300° for 1 hour.
If it browns too much before done, cover it loosely with tinfoil.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss carrots, raisins and pineapple tidbits together.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Stir carefully and thoroughly.
Chill to blend flavors.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown flour in oil, stirring to make paste.
Add meat, salt, pepper, water and tomato sauce to gravy.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: cheese soup
directions: Line strainer with paper coffee filter or cheesecloth layers. Add 1 cup nonfat vanilla yogurt. Set over a bowl and refrigerator for 4 hours. Discard drained liquid.

Combine thickened yogurt and 1/2 cup sifted confectioners sugar. Stir until smooth. Makes about 1/2 cup. Each serving (without sauce) provides: 0 g total fat, 0 mg cholesterol, 130 calories, 3 g protein, 29 g carbohydrates and 150 mg sodium.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove cake from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Yield:
one 10-inch cake.

title: red beans with rice
directions: Slice sausage in rounds; cook in skillet until medium brown. Take out of pan; set aside.
Pour off drippings.
Saute the onion and bell pepper in sausage pan.
Add chili hot red beans and tomato sauce; add garlic and chili powder to taste.
Add sausage.
Bring to boil; turn to simmer.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook rice separately.
Serve bean-sausage mix over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs with 1 1/2 sticks of margarine and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch container.
Whip 1 1/2 sticks of margarine with 2 cups of confectioners sugar and 2 eggs for 15 minutes. Spread on top of crumbs.
Spoon drained pineapple over topping. Place sliced bananas over pineapple topping.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas and sprinkle pecans on top.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix all ingredients except peas; pour into greased mold.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until firm. Unmold on platter and fill with hot green peas.
Top with carrot curls.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Fry beef and onions until meat loses its redness.
Then add tomatoes, sauce, beans and seasonings.
Cook for 1 hour or longer.

title: new reduced fat peanut butter cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter and margarine until creamy.
Beat in sugars, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla until well blended.
Mix in flour until thoroughly combined.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Dip tines of fork into flour and flatten dough in a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Remove.
Cool on wire racks and store in airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take cover off for last 20 minutes.
Makes enough for 6 people.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until done (approximately 8 to 10 minutes). Prepare spinach according to package directions (or simply defrost ahead of time).
Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add carrots and mushrooms.
Cook until crisp and tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, olives and oregano.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water 3 to 5 minutes (do not overcook); drain.
Melt butter and pour 1/2 of butter over vegetables in pan.
Cube cheese; add and toss cheese.
Take rest of butter and crackers; crumble together (in bowl) and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a small size pan (brownie pan).

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 3
ingredients
together;
you
may add 1 egg, if desired (with Jiffy
mix
only).
Pour
in a casserole dish (round or square),	sprayed with nonstick Pam.
Using 1/4 stick of oleo, cut over the	top.
Place
in 375° oven, uncovered.
Bake for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at least 1/2 day.
Beat softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill well, at least 1/2 day or overnight (for 9-inch pie).

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo.
Place a layer of whole crackers on bottom of pan.
Top with half of pudding and then another layer of crackers.
Add the rest of the pudding and finish with layer of crackers.
For best flavor, make a day ahead before serving.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Mix pepper,
onion
and carrots; mix other ingredients. Pour over and marinate
for
12	hours.	Keeps
a long time in refrigerator.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the lettuce should be added last or right before serving, if possible, so that it's crispy.
Yummy, and it goes a long way.
Serve cold.

title: craft clay
directions: Stir together cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water in bowl.
Mix salt and 2/3 cup water in saucepan over low heat until quite warm. Stir cornstarch mixture into salt mixture.
Continue heating.

title: layer pie
directions: Mix pecans, butter and flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream together Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine milk and pudding mix.
Spread over chilled cream cheese layer.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
Sprinkle with chocolate shavings and chopped nuts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease. Simmer with sauce.
Boil noodles.
Put meat sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan, about 3/4 cup sauce, then put layer of noodles, then meat sauce, then half Mozzarella cheese, noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and chili powder.
Add tomatoes, chili beans and salt.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all ingredients well.
Mix together the sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over vegetables.
Let marinate.
Stir once before serving.

title: bisquick coffee cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Set aside after blending.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Add vanilla and beat.
Add Bisquick and beat.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread 1/2 of batter in bottom of pan and then sprinkle 1/2 of sugar and cinnamon on top.
Then add the balance of batter and put the rest of the sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix some powdered sugar and water and drizzle on top.

title: barbecue chestnuts
directions: Blend together well the chili sauce, brown sugar and mayonnaise and set aside.
Take 1 or 2 slices chestnuts and wrap 1 half piece around and put toothpick through bacon to hold together.
Lay each one on cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and put in casserole.
Pour sauce mixture over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for parties.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, heat milk and salt. Add 1/2 cup rice. Cook until tender.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together 3/4 cup evaporated milk, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Add slowly to hot mixture.
Cook until thick.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Mix berries and sugar. Place in a 9x13 pan. Mix flour, salt, shortening and water to make pie crust.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Lay on top of fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Blend in blender for 8 minutes or until blender feels warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Precook chicken in water on top of stove with seasonings.
Take out the packet of seasonings in Mrs. Grass' chicken soup and broth balls.
Put in with chicken.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Put in casserole dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup and Mozzarella.
Put bread crumb stuffing on top.
Sprinkle a little seasoning from stuffing over bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 375° until bread starts to brown.
Uncover and cook another 10 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear washed romaine leaves into bits and place into large bowl.
Add salt, pepper and olive oil to greens (don't add more oil than is needed to coat leaves).
Beat egg and add to middle of salad.
Then add lemon juice and lightly mix to coat.
Add cheese and croutons; mix again.

title: vanilla icing
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Mix in 1/4 cup milk and almond extract.
Add powdered sugar and whip until smooth.
Add 2 cups milk and vanilla pudding.
Beat on high 3 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 7 grain gluten steaks
directions: Soak grains with water at 1 cup level line (1/2 cup more water) overnight (equals 2 batches).
Blend until fine in blender all except flour.
Mix in the flour in a bowl.
May be made into 2 rolls and wrapped in Saran Wrap and frozen.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and boil in broth 45 minutes.

title: heckman's kosher style dill pickles
directions: Take a gallon jar.
Wash small cucumbers and pack into jar whole.
Put a lot of fresh dill on top, middle and bottom as you fill jar with pickles.
Put 1 tablespoon of pickling spice into jar.
Add 6 garlic cloves unpeeled which you have sliced or pierced in several places but do not cut all the way through the clove. Add 6 ounces of white vinegar.
Fill a measuring cup with tap water hot enough to dissolve the salt.
To each cup of water, add 1 teaspoon salt and stir to dissolve.
Pour the water into the jar, cupful by cupful, until the jar is full.
Cover and leave on kitchen counter for 20 days.
They are now ready to eat.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jiffy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add salad dressing and coffee. Mix with spoon until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tarragon chicken with soured cream sauce
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a baking dish just large enough to hold them in one layer.

In a bowl, combine sour cream, onion, bell pepper, lemon juice, parsley, tarragon, sage and salt and pepper to taste; spoon the mixture over the chicken and bake the dish in a preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut bread in 5-inch slices and split slice open (down center). Melt garlic spread and butter together in pan.
Spread mixture on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toast in 450° oven until brown. Serve hot.

title: 1962 fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and batter in saucepan.
Stir to boiling and continue to stir for 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add your candy bars and chocolate chips.
Stir in your nuts, vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Blend your ingredients well.
Pour into a lightly buttered dish and let set up, preferably 24 hours.

title: finger paint recipe
directions: Combine laundry starch and boiling water.
Add glycerin and coloring.
Mix well.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until browned; drain and set aside. Blend margarine and flour to make paste. Add milk and heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add sausage and corn. Pour mixture into a casserole bowl. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican beef skillet
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
In a large skillet, combine ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Cook until beef is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, olives and salt. Add macaroni.
Mix well.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in cheese. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salad
directions: Prepare tongue by rubbing well with soda; scald and scrape. Boil until tender, remove skin, grind or chop.
Add 2 apples, chopped, 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1/2 bunch celery chopped, a little pickles chopped, mayonnaise dressing to make desired consistency. This is a fine substitute for chicken salad.

title: autumn soup(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and celery in 5-quart casserole dish. Microwave at High (100%) until ground beef loses its pink color, 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after half of cooking time.

title: gooey cake and icing
directions: Mix together.
Press into a pan greased lightly with margarine.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a large saucepan, blend first 5 ingredients plus 1 tsp salt.
Stir in 10 cups water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Pack apples into hot jars, leaving 1 inch head space.
Fill jars with hot syrup leaving 1/2 inch head space.
Use spatula or knife to distribute syrup.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath.
Pints-15 minutes or quarts - 20 minutes. Makes 6 quarts.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Mold into ball shape.
Roll in nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Roll out.
Cut and sprinkle tops with sugar.
Also good frosted.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
The more sour the cream, the better the cookie.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo together and then add the cereal and chow mein noodles.
Mix well; cool and coat with powdered sugar.
(Shake in bag.)

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add well-beaten eggs. Add soda to a little hot water to dissolve.
Add half of flour which is sifted with salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mincemeat and rest of the flour.
Drop by spoonfuls an inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from oven while still soft.

title: gourmet stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
Mix rest of ingredients in a large bowl with an electric mixer.
Cut warm potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop potatoes from shell.
Add potatoes to the mixture and beat thoroughly.
Spoon mixture into shells and sprinkle with paprika.
These freeze fine and may be removed from freezer, warmed in oven and served on short notice.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 12 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all three ingredients together.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla for 2 minutes until smooth.
Spread on your graham cracker crust already in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate crust with sugar mixture coating for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken strips
directions: Whisk melted butter and Dijon mustard in shallow bowl.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken strips into butter mixture, then into bread crumb mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 425° for 30 minutes.
If extra crispy is desired, turn after 20 minutes.

title: burgundy beef casserole
directions: Assemble in Dutch oven, cover tightly and cook 4 hours at 300°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and marshmallows together; let stand overnight.
Add apples, pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast the bread and spread with the 2 Tbsp. butter while still hot.
Arrange toast in a buttered pan and sprinkle with the raisins.
Beat the eggs, add salt and all but 2 Tbsp. of sugar. Add the milk and stir to mix.
Pour over the toast and let stand for 10 minutes.
Press the toast down so that it soaks up most of the milk mixture.
Mix the cinnamon with 2 Tbsp. of sugar and sprinkle over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes, until top is brown.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: easy italian beef
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with dry Italian dressing mix.
Cook on low for about 10 to 12 hours.
Halfway through cooking, add jalapeno pepper slices (to taste) and chopped celery. Remove from crock-pot and pull apart.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburger.
Add chicken broth, water, soup mix and celery.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes and frozen mixed vegetables and boil 15 minutes.
Add pasta and boil until pasta is done.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken, put in greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top, skin side up.
Cook in 350 degree preheated oven for one hour.

title: salted peanut crisps
directions: Have oven at 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in.
Stir in peanuts.

title: hot sausage quiche
directions: Prick bottom of pie shell with fork.
Bake about 5 minutes at 350°.
Cook sausage in large skillet until well done.
Drain well on paper towels.
Place sausage in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and seasonings with a wire whisk.
Carefully pour over cheese and sausage in shell (this will be very full).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325° and bake for an additional 45 minutes.
After removing from the oven, let set for 15 minutes before slicing.
Add a tossed salad and asparagus and you have a great supper!
Substitute ham, shrimp, bacon, etc. for the sausage for a change of pace.
